The only reason I'm not giving 5 stars is because of a bug that only happens on Androids. When a Android user is in a call (voice chat in a server, 1 on 1 calls, group calls, etc.) The Android user will suddenly be muted and deafened without warning, and the ONLY way to fix it is to disconnect and reconnect. Which is only a temporary fix because this bug happens at random. And the only way to know is if someone texts you to ask where you went, or if you do the same. PLEASE fix this issue.

Discord has majorly changed my life. Being able to roleplay within large servers of people like me and being able to make chat groups, servers, and open direct messages with people is awesome. I spend most of my time roleplaying or speaking to friends I've made on the app now. I got it a few years back I think, maybe a year or two ago. Frequent updates which enhance your experience within the app. Even small updates you may not notice much make a big difference for everyone! Keep it up, 5 stars.

I love discord, I've used the app for more than 2 years, and im a proud nitro user. However, this new update isn't that good in terms of visuals. This new UI update is cluttered, not nice to look at, and overall a downgrade. The previous UI was better, it's a shame I have to give my favorite app 3 stars because of this... is there any way to make it look like the old UI, by the way?

Excellent mobile version of a much loved app. Most features are available to use. My only personal issue is sometimes the audio can go a little strange after swapping to Bluetooth and back. But I can't really complain about it, it doesn't always happen. All in all it does pretty much everything you need from the desktop version on the mobile platform.

I love discord. I've been using it for years, I'm even a nitro member. Lately however, mobile has been a pretty bad experience. My messages take forever to send sometimes and pictures take forever to upload (no matter how small/large they are). It's pretty annoying considering this is largely a messaging platform. Please fix these issues and you'll get 5 stars from me üòÅüëçüèΩ

I use this app to talk with my friends almost every day. The same functions on the app are just about the same as the PC; however, I have been running into issues with having to redownload the app whenever notifications don't come through. Doesn't matter if I fix the notifications on my phone it still doesn't work. Overall it's still a great app and I enjoy using it :)

Overall, the app is great for communicating with other people. There are a few connection errors that happen every now and again but it's not so often that it runs the whole experience. Voice chat can be a little crazy, although that's probably when a bunch if people are talking at try the same time. It's a good app, and I'd reccomend it over a few others.

I love discord. I have used a lot of chat clients and IRCs over the years and this is definitely the best. There is a little learning curve the first time you use it, but once you get past that everything is intuitive and works amazingly. I use it for chat, video conferencing with friends, streaming games, sharing online content, and more. I can't recommend this enough.

I like it. Having it on your phone surely helps checking out what's going on in your server (and notifications in general). The UI is nice. Suggestion: improve the camera layout and how pictures are taken. A button to open your camera is more than enough and I think a better option, instead of clicking another button to go fullscreen.

Push notifications haven't been working since I've started using Android. I've also noticed on several forums that this has been an ongoing problem since 2018 (2 whole years already!) It's been long enough for this issue to be resolved and discourages me from using Discord in general since I use it most often on my phone. Please fix this already.

Normally, I have no problems with this on my phone, but this is the 2nd time I had to uninstall and re-install in a matter of months after a reboot of my cell. No clue on what's the cause, but Discord will have an issue where its eternally connecting to discord groups or a mass amount of friend icons and names are blanked out. No amount of logging out, clearing it out of the background or what have you fixes it. It only sorts itself out AFTER I reinstall. Is it possible to look into the matter?

I feel this app is amazing for communicating between people. It's easy to use and fun as well. The ability to make your own chatting server for you and your friends is very helpful. Not to mention, the ability to make custom emojis for a server is quite fun to use as well. Overall, I feel using Discord is a very pleasant experience and I highly recommend it to anyone who wants a nice way to have great voice and text communication with people from basically anywhere!

I use it for all my gaming servers and several group chats with friends. 4 stars instead of 5 because the audio doesn't work with Bluetooth (drops out randomly in the middle of calls and plays through speakers, and can't control volume on both phone and laptop), but works fine with corded headphones. Sometimes pictures take upwards of 10 minutes to send, preventing me from sending other messages. Otherwise a great app.

Works very well to keep in touch with friends/associates and for organizational purposes as well. Easy to create, manage, and bot servers and channels. (Dice roller and banana bot are my favorite for completely different reasons). Decent quality streaming/screen sharing capabilities. Not the greatest but certainly not the worst. Also can support dm groups and group voice calls.

It has it's bugs from time to time, but the team is diligent in getting them fixed, and has also added many useful features over the years. It's a great app for staying connected with people online, and very useful for gamers, as it suggests. I've found it's also useful for groups of artists and other creative-minded folks. I recommend this app.

Discord is my go to app for communication while gaming. Its easy to use and has many features for the individual ; volume adjustments,, screen overlay , voice activated and push to talk. For the discord channel creator there are lots of features to customize the interface. I would highly recommend this app. There are many more features I have yet to explore!

Discord has become my second-most-used messaging app, and 'second' only because I don't have everyone I know on it. Searching back to my earliest messages is effortless. I love the variety of emojis. I love the ease of spawning servers and channels. The voice chat is super solid. I've been running a D&D game on Discord for over a year with barely any complaints. Keep it up. Seriously.

One of the best communication apps around nowadays. It's easily accessible on PC/mobile and it performs quite well on both platforms. It also plays host to a number of very strong communities in (and out) of the gaming sphere. Highly recommended to anyone who's interested in joining communities or just wants a reliable way to voice and video chat with friends.

Discord can connect you with millions of people free of charge so long as you have an internet connection. Speaking with friends on video call, voice call, and through text all becomes possible and accessible for nearly everyone. Meet new friends, chat with old ones, and play games with your current buddies. its all possible here on Discord.

Everything is good except for the constantly popping up bug that affected both me and my friends. Sometimes the discord calls would just go silent and you wouldn't be able to talk in the call or even hear anyone. The only fix is to back out and go back in which is very inconvenient because usually you dont even know when you have the bug. Please fix the issue in your next update or hotfix and/or please respond for any type of support.

Excellent app for multiple people playing games, or just having fun; but the audio sometimes crashes for random people in a call/group w/o reason, and you only notice when you are under radio silence. Only option is to reconnect. Also, if you have volume settings set for someone in the call, and either you or them leave and comeback, volume goes up to the max, deafening you.

It's fun to use generally. Syncs well with the pc version. The only thing I can't get to work they way I want is notifications. I just disabled all notifications. I think would be great if there was an option to only show 1 notification from each channel regardless of how many messages are sent in that channel. But other than that it's nice.

Great app that I use for just about anything having to do with gaming. Not only that, I also use it for "Friendcords". Discord just dies randomly, albeit rarely. Mostly a voice chat and screenshare problem. Still way too much CPU usage though, I don't know if that'll ever go away. Not perfect but pretty damn close.

Discord is by far the best app of it's kind that I've ever used. File sharing, voice and video, text chat, your own private server of you want it, and all for free? It's well worth throwing the devs a few bucks for the Nitro upgrade, but even if you don't it's still the current king of communication. I'd give it more stars if I could.

This is all what you need. It is great to find people who wants to play a game it is just imposible to play a game and not going to discord server, competitive information if you're looking for competition info and team up with some players. You must know this app doesn't give you a lot of information how it works but once you got that clear finding how this works you gonna feel free doing what you wanna do. This is the BEST choice if you're looking for something that simply.

It's a great place to chat with friends. It even has voice channels and one can send anything including images and gifs. It even has music channels that enable you to listen to music with others. Yet, I have one problem. It's rated hate NSFW channels even if they were for yof course, a person can choose whether to enter one or not, but those are kids, and they do wild stuff. I try avoiding porn even though I like it, so I despise NSFW channels even if they were for young or older adults.

I love this app and have so many friends on their I never once thought about deleting it. But recently I have updated the app and I don't really like the way it looks.. The text are so close up to my face and all the new details are weird. For example in a two person DM you weren't able to swipe to the side to see who was there but with the new update it does and I don't really like it. Again, I love this app and don't wanna delete it but I would like the old style back.

This app works really well and is one of my favourites for social gaming hubs. I have my own server set up with a group of friends and its growing. I find this mobile app is useful for messaging friends to ask who's playing, so I don't have to be at my PC. It also works well to see if anyone is waiting in any of the voice channels I have set up. Additionally if you have any youtubers you follow that have discord servers, it's good that them posting about videos will pop up on your device too.

I use Discord every day, even not for gaming purposes. I dont have enough money for a console or PC. I just have a phone and even then, Discord allows me to talk to my friends and loved ones quickly and efficiently. Voice chat is clear for the most part but video chat could use a bit of work. I highly suggest this app. That is all.

Discord has made me tons of new friends and enemies for the past year, yeah people can say "I have no life." Which may or may not be true. But with servers, calls that sound perfect. (That depends on your device) through servers you can meet tons of new people and friends. I only have ONE issue with discord, which stops it from giving it a 5 star. You gotta pay Nitro (a monthly payment) to have an animated Profile Picture. But other than the Nitro issue, discord is the one of the best apps ever

This app is amazing! :) I love that they added a group video feature. Now I get to play DnD with my friends online while actually seeing them. The dice rolling bot we were able to add to our server is incredible too (most of us left our dice at our DM's house before COVID). I only wish the desktop version scrolled to the bottom of the conversation rather than you having to adjust to scroll down each time someone posts. Otherwise, a great app for phone and desktop!

Definitely my favorite communication app Discord has a lot of features rarely any other app has, for example the search function. It's amazing. It usually also works without a perfect network connection. The only real downside is the 8MB limit for pictures and videos, it can be very frustrating since most cameras take pictures with slightly above 8MB. It'd be a really cool chance if the limit got set to 8.5MB, it'd save a lot of time and effort.

I've been using Discord for just over two years now, and it is easily one of the best messaging applications on the web. There are paid services that have fewer features than Discord offers for free. Not only that, but it's aesthetically pleasing, a little bit memey, and very user-friendly. The only issue I've had is not getting notifications on occasion.

I love this app a lot it is amazing!! Its really easy to navagate and i love the layout. I just wish there were some options for users who forgot to write down their password for them to see their current password or for those who forgot their password from what i hear it is not easy to get a new one if you forgot it i heard a lot of bad stories about it from my friends. But other then that the app is amazing and would recomend it 10/10!!

It's replaced most my communication apps and even forums. Not just the gaming ones. The app isn't just a flattened web version, it's smartly designed, extremely easy to use, and has so many little features to fit every kind of usage. One issue with the service as a whole and not the app has been minor hitches and dropouts in sound when interacting with users from different areas of the world. Switching servers is a temporary fix. Either way, glorious app for interests/hobbies and gaming.

Was once great. But now its repeatedly making me so many others "hang up" in calls, either muting everyone and us while still being in it or just shutting down all together. Glitches are crazy, you have to pay to send a certain amount of pictures or of varying sizes (I understand paying for emotes in other servers and chats... but pictures? Isnt it a bit ridiculous?) And trying to report these issues comes up with nothing.

my only issue is that message receiving is sometimes bad; if a lot of people are talking at once in one channel of a server, the messages will start to lag. there will be no messages received then 20 messages sent at once, then it goes back to normal. i know it isn't my wifi, because i can watch youtube videos just fine at the same time.

Best messaging app out there! I use it every day! One thing that would help though is possibly a tutorial for new comers. I often find myself having to explain to them how the app works, and it would help if they were given some sort of tutorial when they first create an account, as the app can be a bit convoluted and difficult to learn! Other then that its wonderful!

The recent update has changed the way it looks and stuff too much and is now too small and confusing to look at. Some of the new features can stay such as overlay but please change it back to no 3 sliding sections, it's just plain ugly... Also now when I'm in a DM call I can't see if I'm speaking unless I turn on the overlay, which is just annoying. And there shouldn't be a member list for single DMs, groups I understand but non groups? There's no need. Please make an option to change back...

Havent had many problems. Im in South Korea and use it to talk with my family back in the states. I also use it as a back up for work posted elsewhere, to help in events and RP. My only gripe is that the streaming doesnt capture sound because im not running windows 10, but 8.1. It just seems weird that it's programmed that way.

I mainly use the app for communication with gaming friends and group chats ( average 6-8 hours). Found the app incredibly reliable for talking and keeping in contact with friends. Took me a couple seconds to figure out how it works but found it very easy to navigate between multiple groups. Better than other apps I've used in the past.

Fantastic app, haven't found bugs whilst using it, probably more stable than my computer. Has most of the features that are available on computer, don't think you can share screen on phone but you can view others live share. Works well with data doesn't consume much either. Can do video calls on the phone. Audio settings aren't as customisable but then again why would it be. Would easily recommend to anyone.

I've had some of the best days of my life while using this app. For me, this is the best communication tool. It is very costumeizeble with all of the bots (Bots for server management,for memes, games, notifications,music etc.), ranks, colors, nicknames, the ability to make emojis etc And, most importantly, THE BEST audio on the market. The developers really know their stuff, there are a lot of little details and references that makes this app even better. (Try coping your name by clicking on it)

Of all the chat room apps on any platform I've ever seen, I've never seen one better than Discord. It's fast and reliable and user friendly and is downloadable on just about any platform you can think of, in addition to being very well structured. I've used it not just to keep in touch with friends I have around the globe, but to actually make friends around the globe. I'd recommend it over Zoom as a means to stay in touch during the pandemic, especially in casual settings.

Discord is one of the best apps I have personally ever used. It never fails, no connection issues. It has multiple functions to help adjust the audio settings to something that suits your needs. It's super user friendly also. Discord is just overall a top shelf, 5 star quality app. It could be considered foolish using any other.

Very user friendly. Discord is constantly making improvements, and listens to its consumers. While the application may have some issues from time to time, such as spotty connections and the like, it does not affect its overall performance. Often, it is merely the company running maintenance. Definetely worth it.

Love it! Discord is the best app for chats, especially group ones where you're constantly going off on tangents and things. Think the old internet forums where you had threads and BAM! That's what you've got, only instant, direct, and perfect for smartphones or tablets (and even computers). The fact that for computer there's also a web based one is amazing. So many chats in one place! ‚ù§Ô∏è

I've used Discord every day of my life for over five years. It is user-friendly, cross platform, and has a host of features that support guilds, gaming, rp, remote lessons for my art classes and more. I use this to communicate to people threefold more often than any other social media platform, both business and casual.

Honestly, 100%, unless you are doing international communications, this app does everything Skype does but better...for free. Voice, video, file sharing, text, in an easy to operate layout. The only reason I first got Nitro was for the larger file sharing, however i found quickly it made all of my calls even better. What else can i say besides that but, unless i count Chrome, there is no app i use more. NO CONTEST!!!

It's really good in terms on communication even though sometimes we cut out or just can't hear each other idk if it's the app or just something wrong on our end but anyways it's fun because you can get bots for servers that can allow rpg and music and many different games. It's overall a great app as well as it is safe! You can decline any people you don't know to be friends with you. I know some apps that don't have that and it's weird but I do enjoy discord.

Excellent service provider. Does occasionally have hiccups such as service disruptions due to being overwhelmed or problems with picking up microphones properly, but the support when such things happen is fast and effective. Personal security is so well protected that when i lost my account, i had to make a new one after deleting my old account. All in all, a good long term investment.

This app is really good. In discord, you can chat with friends, voice chat, text, video chat, and screenshare specific windows or the entire screen. You can choose what mic/webcam you want to use. You can join discord servers or make your own and build a community. Most games have their own discord servers with thousands of users. You can friend people and make groupchats. However, there are some predators on here, as in every user based program tho. I would download it if I were you!

I love this app, but it could be a LOT better. Just to name some issues and improvement suggestions, for one, the voice chat has gotten worse. Sometimes all the audio is randomly cut and I have to leave and rejoin the vc to hear people again. Using emojis can freeze and crash Discord, plus it happens very often. There should be an option to view emojis as an image on the app like the PC version. If Discord covered these flaws, this app could be 5 stars, but until then, three stars it is.

Most useful app I have! Not only can you send messages (and emojis, pictures, gifs, and web links), make calls, video calls, and join servers... you can also stream a game in a personal chat or in a server, share your screen with the person you're talking with so that they can see what your doing on your device, and (my favorite) you can share any application window such as an internet browser so that you can watch videos with someone! üòÄüòÅ üíúüíúüíú

It's effecient, but there's quite a few things missing. No read receipts, certain file sizes cant be sent, & the voice chat is very inconsistent. That being said, if you're a gamer, it's most definitely worth it. Being a free service, you can do a plethora of things as far as servers, groups, roles etc.

I've used Discord as my primary platform of communication for years now, and the company has always proven reliable, offering many desirable and innovative features that make Discord convenient and interesting to use, and they're always working hard to add more to it. Whether you're looking to chat with friends, connect with people about your favorite things, or just source some choice memes, Discord has something for everyone!

This application is more than any chat app. Average application weight, with high performance and reliable security. It can be used from casual to enterprise level. You can even make an automated reporting system out of it using the API and Webhook. Server and room is scalable. Permission can be managed based on role, exclusively. Server upgrade is worth it. It's perfect.

It works pretty well, but there are times where it times out, I guess? One minute I'm talking with my friends and then another I'm screaming into the void, wondering if they all died because the app acts as though they're not speaking. A quick hop out and then back into the server fixes it for awhile, but it shouldn't be happening regardless

Discord is the best comms app, mainly because it's so much more then that. I run my own YouTube community out of one, as well as managing multiple others for other channels. The features provided are a show case to it's excellence. While I give it 5*s, there are still things I have gripes with. 1) I'd really like a Category within a Category System for better management on my communities. 2) Boosting a community to unlock more features is expensive. Really expensive unfortunately. 5*s still.

Discord is highly helpful when it comes to communicating with people in large groups. As a person that games, we find discord the most effective way of communication. I recommend this for communicating with people that live in other countries as well. We have people that play that live in Canada, the United States, London, Ecuador, and Mexico. We can all talk to each other at the same time with discord. Good job at creating an app that actually does what they tell you it is supposed to do.

Great app with a user friendly interface, though it does take some getting used to because of how unique it is. I can't say I have ever run into any glitches, which is impressive. The quality of the app is more than enough proof that the developers care about their product with a passion. Probably my favorite social media app because it has zero advertisements and gives you only what content you want to see.

There's a bug for the voice channel. I talk with my friends and sometime my suddenly disconnected. Its not like disconnected, it still connected but everybody can't hear me and I can't hear them too. I reconnect the voice channel and it's fine. But man, I don't want reconnect the voice channel so many times. Please fix this issue

So much better than having to sacrifice my valuable personal data to Facebook. Also the seamless ability to quickly post a file in a chat is a sheer blessing. Any music I make may be far from amazing, but it's really nice to be able to share it with my closest friends so easily. Lastly, the vast options not just for customization but also for functionality is a true testiment as how much this app is built for the user. So many things are done right w/this app, & deserve a very solid 5 stars.

userName: H E E H E E
content: Honestly Discord was where I spent a lot of my time online with my friends. Its turned bad now. The system the use to reset your password doesnt work, it says "Password does not match." (After I changed it)I had some fond memories on there that are now all gone because of that. The system itself is ok at best. Bots were a pretty cool concept. The design of the app is horrid IMO the text is so small, and the black and grey colour scheme hurts my eyes. Everything isnt organised nicely either.

I rate this 5 stars because it is such a good app. I use this on a daily basis. One downside i am having however is that i would love an option to tick all boxes or cross all boxes on the role permissions thing. I hate having to manually do it to my channels. But this app is really cool because you can add fun bots to the server. Anyways, i love this app!

Can't watch streams now... all they do is refresh no matter what connection I'm on. Edit: for an app that prides itself on connecting people, it seems to fail at that. Notifications barely come through without mute on, and it's not just me and my phone. App has to be closed and reopened to send messages more often than not. Update after update has not fixed these issues.

Push notifications are a little spotty, but otherwise I haven't had any significant problems with the app. It's Discord, if you're here, you probably know what it is and what to expect. One of the best messaging services out there right now, but this particular iteration of the app isn't perfect. Still extremely usable and better than any alternatives though

Quite well made app. It does its job and it's being constantly updated but I feel like there is still not everything "phonish" enough about it. A lot of features seem like they are more optimized for the PC rather than a mobile device. Anyway - still a pretty good app for what it can allow you to do on the go. <3 4 Discord

Coming from vent, TeamSpeak, Skype, mumble... Discord is truly king. Perfect for gaming, socializing, or more unique uses (i keep up with a charity through their discord channel). The free-to-use option exceeds expectations alone, and the premium option gives some great perks. If you have a group text with your friends and havent switched over to a discord channel, you're missing out on a huge opportunity. Seriously, this program is phenomenal.

One of the best social apps available, great for chatting with groups of people who have similar interests and also for personal one-on-one messaging. Has plenty of emotes if you want to use them and also allows for file and link sharing with previews. Has voice calling features and a desktop version of the app as well (which I use)

Outstanding app for gamers to use and stay connected. Setting up your own server is fairly easy and can be done quickly to get it up and running. Allowing the addition of Categories with Channels lets you customize your server how you wish. The ability to assign roles to members is awesome for gamers who utilize teamwork. Lastly, they are constantly updating the app and over the years that I've used it I may have ran into 1 issue which support quickly responded to my message and helped.

The app works great for 90% of discord functions. I'm able to message my friends, speak with them if required, and do nearly anything I always do. Some issues (very minor) include working poorly over Bluetooth; my Bluetooth devices that have calling capability (such as my car) treat the discord calls as a voice call and mess everything up. Very minor issue for a great app!

The app's voice chat function is in desperate need of fixing. The volume sliders typically don't work. It also resets individual users to full volume when they enter the call- really hurts the ears- especially with music bots, which are insanely loud by default and typically have to leave/rejoin several times during a call. Otherwise it's a very fast, pleasant, and easy to use app.

i love discord, believe me, but i use it for mobile, and it's outlook: not so good. my phone is old, and it can get very glitchy sometimes. i haven't had any problems until these new updates, call and message wise. I'm having a hard time connecting to calls, having breaks in speech, and even not playing any audio.. it gets frustrating. the app had to close itself multiple times due to this. As of now, no more audio is playing from calls.

Let me tell ya, Discord is amazing. I have experienced little to no bad times on this app, and it's very simple to understand once you get the hang of what's going on. Not to mention the friends I've made on this platform as well. So many people have showed up onto my server and I've become good friends with many of them! It's also a good way to keep in contact with friends I have at school. I legitimately, unironically believe that Discord is one of the best social media platforms available.

Huge fan of the PC version, mobile one though, giving me lots of connectivity issues, when I'm in a private call it will randomly switch to speaker mode on it's own, completely stop transmitting and receiving audio, or straight up disconnecting me and automatically reconnecting when I tab back into the app. Those issues plus it sometimes doesnt notify me I'm being called, until i tab open the app, then it shows as if someone is calling me, although it happened hours ago. Pls fix it sucks.

As with most apps on iOS and Android, the latter gets a half-baked, barely supported feature set. The core functionality is good (text and basic voice channels), but more advanced features are a crapshoot. The only input method that works on my Pixel 3XL is push to talk, no matter how many of the workarounds I try. My mic quality on mobile is garbage compared to every other device despite it sounding flawless on other apps. Speaker creates an endless feedback loop for the other end. ECT ECT.

I've been using Discord for... over 2 years now. It's where I met and how I still talk to all of my friends, and really where I go for all my human interaction. I've never had any problems with it beyond understandable minor annoyances, and honestly I'm grateful to have it. Thanks, Discord, and I look forward to being here for a lot longer.

Discord is amazing but it's often prone to bugs and glitches. Nothing that a reboot mostly can't fix. However prevalent issue that occur are sound blast through speakers instead of headphone when they're connected. Often people's volumes are erratic. Push to talk can be glitch and has to be turned on. Beware of battery heat. Beyond a few issue it's still a good program that's more often than not reliable. Best used with WiFi.

Convenient, always remembers past posts, updates are always full of great new features that always make discord easier and more reliable to use! Please always keep history, sub categories, and pins, keep up the good work. (And I) will always recommend discord to everyone I know! I actually love it so much I almost applied to work for you (but I live very fast away). And here I mostly use it for writting, and interacting with my INFJ support group. Discord is the perfect ground for communities!

I got this app to talk to my brother one day, and we have used it since to keep in touch with our gaming team and friends all over the world. I wasn't expecting anything, and I found a great communication experience. Now, it's one my main means of communication when playing video games, and would definitely suggest it to anyone who needs an unintrusive call app during online play.

Absolutely amazing, I've been using discord for around 5 years now and only a few major bugs have happened which caused nobody to be able to use discord for small amounts of time, however other than this the app is great, met many mates on it had fun with others and joined many many groups. I can recommend this app to anyone who needs a communication app, it's simple fun and easy to use. Being able to customise your own server and profile is also a great add-on! Have a good day!

Good overall app, but I'm going to list some gripes here as well. No push-to-talk button on the overlay Switching from push-to-talk to voice activity or vice-versa has the tendancy of cutting out all sound without notification and requires a rejoin of the voice channel to fix it. QR codes have a lot of security issues. This app has a lot of security issues. It seems like every month theres a new exploit that threatens to install a trojan or compromise your account. Out of characters...

Discord is a great way to connect with people around the world. The server feature allows for tidy seperations of groups and is incredibly useful for a variety of groups. I've run charities, parties, GSAs, etc. Plus this is really good for ppl with ADHD: its organization. One feature I wish was available is a screenshare aspect for mobile as well as desktop, and a steadier voice channel connection, but otherwise this app is great to use, and once you get the handle of it, very user-friendly.

Highly modular, user created chat and voice rooms with variable permissions through roles. Server bots are supported. Saturated with useful functionality, bundled with an easy to use interface. Dark mode is not only optional, but default. Exceptionally non-intrusive as freeware. Service quality is equally impressive. Active communities are abundant. Cross platform between mobile and desktop. This app deserves 5 stars, without a doubt.

For beginners Discord might take some time to get used to. But that aside, it is a very well developed app, that is centered around providing the best quality calls and video calls while gaming, studying etc. Recommend. P.s lately there have been added a lot of new content that might load the CPU, GPU and RAM but some of the settings allow to tone the stress down. Basically performance over visuals.

Y'all made it almost unusable for tablets. I can't see my pings and I can't scroll through my chats without some serious effort. I know it isn't my screen either because I can have two apps open on my Samsung Galaxy Tab E. I can't run it on the right of my screen since this last update. I love this app and will never stop using it but make it more mobile friendly. It's not fair for us to miss out because of the PC users.

The development team is awesome, helpful, listens to the community, and is the exact opposite of Skype. In fact, this program is the opposite of Skype. It works, people move on video, you can hear every independent yell and nose-whistle of your friends going 0/7 against an adc in the midlane because they obviously "main mid". 10/10 voice/video/server chat. Delete Skype.

Has major problems when opening a YouTube video that is linked to a specific time stamp. Usually requires two to three tries before it goes to that time. Other times it will start the vid at the beginning, sometimes playing an ad first. Also had issues with microphone on headphones, but those seem to be patched. Otherwise a mostly good experience.

I've been using Discord for years, and it's service only gets better and better. The devs actively listen to the community, get rid of clunky features, add more features -- and they understand their user's needs. I've become more thankful for Discord since COVID, especially because the dumpster fire that are other video call services. Discord made the natural transition from voice to video to game streaming, and there's nothing else like it.

Overall very good experience, my only complaint is that when I'm on call with someone, it sometimes cuts me out and I can't hear anything on the other end and they can't hear anything from me. I constantly have to exit the call and then go back in for it to work again. It happens maybe once or twice in a 2-3 hour call, and I always update the app when I check for updates. Other than that, it's a breeze.

I genuinely do love this app, but mobile needs a lot of tweaking to fix the common glitches found on Discord mobile, such as: people can't hear you anymore and you can not hear them & the only way to fix it is to rejoin the call if you even come to realize it's happened, sometimes you'll end up talking to yourself a lot before realizing.

This is the best app, period. So many awesome features are constantly being added, just when I think "How can Discord be better?" Discord single-handedly allowed my buddies and I to get off of Facebook, to have a place to talk about our interests and make dumb memes and emoji. I decided a while back that a company that did this without selling my information or shoved ads down my throat deserves my money, and haven't looked back since I got Nitro to support these amazing people.

Really buggy. My friends and I will be dropped when using voice chat all the time. The app doesn't seem to have a good connection with any of my Bluetooth headphones, sometimes it will just stop outputting through the headphone and start with the phone itself. Needs a lot of fixed for that but the chat features not bad.

I have been using Discord for almost five years at the time of writing this review. I originally started using Discord because Skype was not working properly for me, and oh boy am I happy about moving to Discord. The ability to create servers can connect users in a way other apps just simply can't do. I use Discord all the time when playing video games with friends, and with fast and pretty reliable servers makes calls much better. Highly recommended for all gamers wanting a better experience.

There are many things that are awesome, but some things that are not preferable. Impossible to delete old conversations (bad memories) unless you delete the user, and if you do, but later re-add them, the past is all still there. Not worth deleting your words line by line if you can't delete theirs too.

You probably already know what discord is, so I'll keep it short. It is the single best messaging and calling app on the market. You can make servers for you and your friends, you can join servers with 100s or even 1000s of people to talk about something you have in common (videogames, pop culture etc.). It is all around amazing and I would recommend it to anyone. Just get it.

Discord is free, non ad funded and very user friendly. It is easy to use and set up. All services are free to use with an optional "Nitro" subscription option to support the developer in return for bigger file upload size and animated emotes. The calls are high quality, no lags or audio quality issues. Would 100% recommend not just for gamers but other uses too.

With constant improvement updates, this app gets better all the time. It's one of the few mobile apps I've seen where the functionality is so close to the same level as their desktop equivalent, and over the past year the scope of what you can do with it has expanded. Probably the best community connection platform I've ever used.

Use this over Zoom, Teamspeak, Skype, etc. If quality is what you want, you got it. Need to find a community but it's super niche? You'll find it. Worried about security issues? This company can't afford a data leak, the security is phenomenal compared to its rivals. TL;DR Discord is the best chat service out there. So long as you're 13+ years of age.

I use discord all the time. I really like it, but it still has a lot of bugs. lately when I've been doing private calls, it randomly kicks me out sometimes, and also sometimes audio stops working completely, so I have to leave the call and join again. another bug that has been going on for a long time, is that notifications sometimes come very late, or dont come at all. Please remedy this :)

After 2 years having this on my phone it only asked me now to rate it. I found some of my closest friends and relationships on here. Not going to be that guy who rates 4* because of it, but there's a couple of nagging flaws like android being behind on updates (/shrug taking forever to arrive comes to mind) and interface being changed a lot, especially recently, but those are just growing pains. I would have rated this 3* due to screen burn in but that was recently fixed. Excellent chatting app.

It's a great app for communication regardless of what you're doing; be it gaming, exercising, or just to sit down, and enjoy a conversation. On top of that you are able to see all other participants in a group as well as their optional online status, their nickname, picture, and even what they're doing most of the time. Its screen share is phenomenal as well. Very seamless to put it short, and its updates regularly. (The update notes are hilarious, and Wumpus is cute.)

This is probably one of the easiest apps to use, I've never had troubles with it. The UI is very user friendly. The call quality is top notch, you can hear your buddies mics very easily and clearly in a group call. Even when you're playing a game, the audio is perfect and the overlay makes it very nice to know who's talking.

Great for MMO game social interaction off game. Havent used it for much more than that but seems to be a multi functional and versatile app. Not sure what could be improved on specifically, but i feel like it could be tweaked to be better in miscellaneous ways. Other than that, works well for what i need it to work for so I'm satisfied

Discord is the ultimate group chat for gaming. While it's known as an invaluable resource for PC, most people don't realize just how useful the app can be. Rather than only receiving messages while at your game station, the app keeps you notified of that upcoming raid or game night wherever you might be. Definitely worth downloading. On top of that, having a secondary mobile device nearby enables you to send chats with Google voice without tabbing out of a game, so you can always stay focused.

My only complaint is that you can't directly search for a user like you can on desktop. The search bar is there, but it never finds the user. I've spoken with many others who have the same issue. The only work around is to send a friend request to the user, and then when you search that user's name, it will bring them up and allow you to message them.

Fantastic. Easy to use app, options are quickly available and problems are easily solved by Google. I honestly suggest it to everyone as an alternative to WhatsApp and Skype. With one account I can be on my favorite streamers chat and in a group chat at the same time! Easy for coordination, able to stream games for interested friends, play tabletop game or stay up to date.

I like being able to group chat with my friends on here and sharing pictures and videos. The only problem with the app is the volume. I can't turn it up very loud. There are a lot of times I can barely hear my friends on it or they can't hear me. There are times when the volume goes really low and I have to end the call and re-enter the chat. Sometimes it works and the volume goes back on and sometimes it doesn't. I also like live streaming games.

As someone who used Messenger, KiK, Google Hangouts, Textfree, and many other group messaging apps, this is by far my favorite. Several bugs still exist but they're being squashed daily, and Discord is one of the most versatile underappreciated apps to be and continues to improve. My favorite feature would have to be between the Discord Chat Overlay, and the ability to seamlessly switch from PC to Android mobile during a call. My friends are often amazed at the smooth transfer. 9.8/10 imo

It is a great way to communicate with players in games that don't have in game chats. It's also cool that there are some games that have game emojis. The only reason it doesn't get 5 stars, is because it is outside the realm of the game, and if you don't know there is a channel for your game there is really no way to contact people in the game, unless the game has a chat within the game. A person I knew from another game gave me the info I needed for a new game, and you need to be invited.

Best Chat service. A free service that let's you create you own server for no cost. Easy drag and drop for pictures and files on desktop. Integrates with many games too. It just works well. Had the upgraded (monthly cost) when they used to include a bunch of free monthly games (think Xbox gamepass or origins gamepass), but they have discontinued the games and lower the sub cost, so I have discontinued my subscription. I still love discord though, great service.

Discord is fantastic. However, I experience frequent issues with detecting audio configuration: the root cause may be OS driver updates however discord is far from "robust" in this regard. It often leads to several layers of volume sliders (OS, discord in OS, discord global, user specific). Ironically, a major improvement to this issue could be simply implemented with a specific volume slider for all notification sounds. This would be my primary recommendation to earn 5 stars.

I've been using discord for over 3 years now as my primary mode of communication with all of my close friends. In those 3 years they have added so many amazing updates that give the program more function and a better quality of life. If your looking for a good video or audio calling application I would strongly recommend discord.

Great performance and quality. App is the single best for any kind of communication and community. Only problem is some settings that are changed (such as the new layout) that I can't revert. Another issue is that I keep constantly having to update it for the exact same thing (this may be a play store issue). Other than that, there's very few bugs and everything works smoothly.

Best overall communications app hands down. This is coming from a Ventrilo and Mumble enthusiast for over a decade. Has some performance hiccups that aren't the dev's fault. The framework Electron needs to optimize and this won't be a battery killer. It can be difficult to use at first, just try to understand the separation of concerns of the menu as you peruse it.

I've only had minor problems with Discord on both PC and the app so that why I'm rating it a 4/5. It'd actually be closer to a 4.5/5 but I can't do that. It's a great source to connect with friends or even meet new ones. The UI is simply and nice to look at. Voice and Video chat is really smooth. Kinda a must-have tbh

I really appreciate the fact that we get to talk to other players in our own communities and set up different gatherings for radar and community day! it helps out being able to get to know some of the people that are out playing and enjoying the exact same games that I do. The nice thing is there are multiple levels of games that you can play and be on discord and keeping in contact with other players which helps you sometimes to progress in the game that you are playing.

This app is so good, what with the bots and all the fun stuff. The experience of creating a new server yourself first-hand is just so interesting. This is by far the best communicating app I have ever seen. Even the new way of calling in voice channels is sensational. As a gamer, this app is very useful for when me and my friends play online games together. The quality of the call is just so good, though there are some bugs sometimes where I hear echos of my own voice. Overall, this app is great

Discord on PC is fantastic. However the phone app needs serious work. They must come up with more phone friendly interfaces. Also for some reason the sound quality is a little better than awful. Please note,this is for the phone app only. The PC app is, as said above, fantastic and does not have these issues.

It's amazing! It allows me to message my friends way easier, and I met alot of new people through public servers. Im online so much, and discord has basically become my home. The only problem is that I mostly use mobile, and when I'm creating custom roles, I'm only limited to certain colors. I want to have a variety of colors for the roles, so I just don't want to be stuck with those. It would be really great if you added custom role colors to mobile.

Discord works largely thanks to insular communities who help troubleshoot. However, using help and navigating text instructions can get tricky. I wish there was a manual that covered basic profile setup and use. I thought I added pronouns to my profile, when it seems I've only changed my profile in that channel. Confusing! Overall, the opportunity to open an instant communication group is a great feature that fosters collaboration and camaraderie.

Really great option for voice chat. Nice that it makes it easy to video and add links to chat. I do wish you could control how much the mic pics up. Other voice chats when you change the slider it actually changes how much background noise is picked up first then your voice but not so in discord. Would also like to see options to add your own personal photo for your profile and customize more.

I really like this app and it's really helpful - however, it almost never gives me notifications for when someone messages me. I've checked through all the settings in Discord and my phone, but no matter what, I don't get notifications. It's a little annoying, but other than that, the app is amazing and I would definitely recommend it.

The app is nice I love it, for messaging at least. The problem is that the calls just don't work for me either I have an echo I'm unintelligible or can't be heard at all. Whenever I join a call my phone picks ups the voices of everyone else and plays it through my phone, push to talk helps but then when I talk nobody can understand me, using a mic also helps but then the app picks up no audio at all. So maybe this is just a problem on my end but thought I might as well as leave a review.

Discord is amazing. From letting creators have YouTube content to put out, Twitch streamers being able to communicate with their audience, to just having the app for fun, Discord is amazing! The reason I gave Discord a 4star rating, instead of a 5star, is because I haven't explored all of Discord, and have only been using it for around 3weeks. But so far Discord is amazing, and I really recommmend it as an app, but you have to remember that you have to get used to it, like any other new thing.

Great app but I recently switched phones and got a Galaxy S10. Whenever I try to talk in a Voice Call or chat, my microphone is really quiet and no one can hear me. There's an option to change communication mode and everyone can hear me but then it makes everyone else sounds horrible. And even then whenever I'm in a call for too long, my voice sounds robotic and I have to end the call. There's also a bug were sometimes if you even accidentally press the emoji button it freezes my app.

This app is great for when you want to talk to your friends without having the low quality sound of in game voice chat. My only issue is that the audio stops coming through every now and then, so I have to leave the voice channel and then go back into it. It fixes the problem but it can still be an annoyance. Otherwise great app.

I literally use this whenever possible for group chat needs, especially those that will go a while. Its easy to use, easy to organize and meets my needs perfectly. Im only rating this 4 stars simply because of the file size limit. I was prompted to subscribe or join nitro and I can't afford to do that, so i either can send the files or I have to use a different app to do it. Either way, if I was able to truly make this my one and only stop, id give it a full 5 stars.

I use discord everyday but it does have a wide range of problems with disconnecting or freezing midway through calls and screen shares, most of the issues I experience have already been complained about so I'll just say that this app is overall perfects for keeping in touch with gaming buddies and what not, but at some moments can be a bit of a hassle to deal with. ‚úåÔ∏è

I've mostly had a good experience using the Discord app. I can use it to stay in contact with people on the move, and keep talking to people online in a pinch when home internet dies. Only issues I've really had is in places where internet connection is spotty, the chat function can work really odd - resending days old messages, retrieving other people's messages out of order, etc. But nothing too bad

Discord is easily one of the best made apps for chat I've ever used. it's the best mix of things like ventrilo Skype and other things. However, recently it seems there had been a report that they will be releasing an algorithm that checks severs for "forbidden words" and can delete servers and accounts. And it's sad to see more anti free speech spreading. More over considering I thought discord better than this.

Generally a good app. Definitely better than the other options in this category. My main issue is that it can be frustrating on slower connections. Luckily my internet is faster now but back when I was on a 10mbps connection it took forever just to load messages sometimes. I hope that gets figured out eventually.

Discord is an all-in-one platform that provides a plethora of well designed qualities such as screen sharing (You can share your whole screen, or one specific window if you dony want other things you are doing to be visible), live streaming for those gamers looking for an audience, group calling restricted to invitations on a private server you create, and more. All of that comes extra, because discord at its base is a wonderful chat platform with great voice and video call quality. A+++

The app is great! They added screen sharing to the regular server calls so now i can stream my games and art streams whenever and wherever! The only issue i really have is when ever is act up. It's not all the time but whenever ot does happen i sometimes think it's my internet and not the app. I would go upstairs and turn in and off the wifi so many times only to realise it's the app. Other than that it's a great app to use.

discord is great, but the voice calls still have a lot of problems on mobile. They seem to cut out a lot, and on occasion (after an hour or so) they'll just make one person very loud and the other very quiet, and the only way to fix it is by hanging up and calling again. The text chat is excellent though.

What can I say that hasent already been said this app is for everyone. Whether your a gamer, furry, or just like the weirder side of things. This app is for you. If you are part of a community and want to expand it, this is where you go. If you're wanting to start a community this is where to go. If you want to chat with friends and hangout when you're oceans apart this is where you go. This app if for everyone, so if you dont have Discord get it and join or start something great.

It is typically a wonderful experience I think it has single handedly revolutionized the way that people contact with each other via gaming or otherwise I do wish there were a few more features that I would be a little bit more user friendly as there a been a quite a few occasion that I didn't know how this feature work and most of the time someone asked to teach me.

It is very fluent and easy to switch between channels and splitting up teams for custom games, I've had psuedo meetings on it because the audio quality is great, one problem that only I seem to have amongst my friends and have found similar problems online is discord will randomly drop me from any channel or call while I'm using the app on my phone. There is no exact amount of time between each drop and the frequency is unpredictable but expected. Overall love discord. I'd give 4.4, 5 for a fix

Honestly, this is my favorite app to communicate with my friends considering this whole Pandemic we're all going through. I love the UI and the simplicity of it, while at the same time it's very user friendly and allows a lot of customization within servers! And the recent addition of video chat to servers is awesome!

App was great on my old galaxy phone, but I updated to the pixel 4 XL and I suddenly (apparently, I've never heard it myself) get horrible white noise coming from my mic. I tried messing with discord sound settings in app, but my current best solution is to enable push to talk only, and immediately sprint to my PC so friends don't have to hear static. This problem only occurs with discord, mic seems to work great for cellular calls, Snapchat, Facebook messenger calls, etc. Any help would be üî•üòú

Excellent, well built app. UX is beautiful and intuitive. The company and staff are awesome, and seem like a very wholesome group and culture. The Discord communities can be incredible and almost any hobby or interest has several discord communities to join. The audio and video calling is exceptional, and they support their platforms with regular updates to the client applications. I truely believe that this is one of the most innovative and exceptional platforms in existence.

I love Discord. It's my all in one platform for connecting with friends, exploring hobbies, and following content creators. The Discord team works tirelessly to provide the best service possible to everyone whether you choose to pay or not. Their subscription model is very affordable and packed with sharable features that can bennefit your friends and entire servers. I hope this platform never goes away or loses its way as it continues to grow.

One of the best apps on my phone. Simple Lightweight application and is the ONLY voice over internet service I have ever used that has consistent and clear audio all the time. The app also has video calling and screen streaming features that work really well as well. It's like slack for gamers but better and with better servers. Highly recommend this chat app to anyone looking to chat by voice online.

Great all around performance, but loses 2 stars for the constant 3 to 6 dropouts of the voice capability within every session. Our family group consistently has each member "going out (disconnect) and coming back in again" (reconnect) at random times regardless of what type of equipment /headphones/air pods, etc. we run individually. It is frustrating!

We moved to discord what feels like forever ago for our online group. Voice calls stay pretty stable even with a large group of 8-15 people. Having a text chat readily available has been great for people without mics to communicate in the same program. The use of different channels has been great for organizing conversations and all around is a great app to use for gaming groups.

Discord is great for game chat, video chat, group chats and is just generally a great communication app. I'll admit that updates to the app come slower here on the Google Play store in comparison to Apple's App Store. However, I will not hold this against the developers. Discord holds far more advantages than other messaging apps for group interactions, as separate channels can be set up within each server for different topics eg. a general chat room can be separated from links to videos.

userName: The Docky Nazers loli penetrator while bokeing it
content: Pretty easy to learn, though got some things it could express a little but its fine. Got a lot of my friends to switch over to it now its all we use, cool how I can show what I'm doing when it's either playing games or listen to music. But two complaint I have is that, one i wish I could send bigger files without nitro as when I'm sending a pic or a meme I have to explain what it is and ruining the joke. Two wish I could show my screen without having to livestream with others like in a DM.

I've been using Discord for half a decade and I've been dreading that moment when a useful of software becomes bloated and unpleasant (skype, office, insert your own example here). So far Discord has mostly managed to keep feature creep at bay (store and other premium features are easily ignored if you dont need them) while improving voip quality to arguably the best consumer version availiable. I hope that in another 5 years I still use it with the same joy as I do now!

Voice chat experience has not been as good as I remember, especially the past few updates. When I'm in a mixed party chat between friends on Xbox and on PC we end up using the Xbox party chat vs Discord, the Xbox party chat quality is much better in clarity and sound quality. I love the Discord app and I hope the voice chat quality improves to make the experience the best all around.

Great texting app and good calling app. While texting and calling are a bit jankier than the desktop counterpart, calling on mobile is a good amount jankier. Often these problems arise in the middle of calling, consisting of frequent cutting and sometimes making you and your friend very quiet and discord displaying a constant reconnecting status. However, these problems can be fixed with restarting the call/app, so these problems are more of a minor inconvenience. 4/5 would and have recommended.

I have been using Discord for a few years now and I have enjoyed the application's convenience and ease of use. I initially got an account after being dissatisfied with Skype, but I have 0 regrets about switching. Discord is great for group chats and IMing friends as well as conference calls and livestreaming games. I hope the company's continued willingness to keep the servers at peak performance whether or not you're a Nitro user.

It is what it says. Voice, video, user run servers for every kind of group imaginable. Voice and video quality isn't the greatest in comparison to some other services more specialized in those things, but Discord works as advertised as a generalist program popular for gaming as well as social networking. For me Discord is a ubquitous service that I use everyday.

I love Discord and use it since roughly 2017 and I've been connecting to a lot of friends that turn into my closest friends ever! But I have a few proplems like: -Opening a folder to get to a Server but then to be scrolled back to a previous one that is open. - The limet on file size. I keep alot of my files on Discord for storage and if a file is too big, it gets harder to keep track of things. - Previews don't work most of the time for a Website me and most of my friends use. But thats just me

Discord is the best app for communication. That could be either while playing games or for just a gc or a server that u want to create. Its really simple to use and there's no lag or delay between messages whatsoever. Its a great platform for communication. The only thing that's a little annoying is that you can't send anything over 8MB if you don't have Discord Nitro. But u can just create a mediafire link to send.

This is a very well built app to chat with friends and gather the whole group for some conversations and keeping everyone together. You can play games, roleplay, or even just share what's on your mind. And with the many bots that can be added, the experience can be enhanced to increase the possibilities of fun.

I've always loved Discord as a way to stay in touch with friends. Some features I'd like to see. Analytical options to better understand how your server is being used. To find out things like, who is active (to distinguish active members, active readers and completely inactive users), most popular channels/ frequently used, most popular roles as a way to better understand your audience demographics etc. Another row for frequently used emojes or a way to favourite emojes. Animated loadscrean.

I truly love discord as a voice/gaming/communication platform. I believe that there could be better ways to simplify privacy options and better personalisation, and for a five year old company they're doing amazing. I just feel that there's a stagnant issue that engrosses individuals who play a variety of games and would benefit from having more options for multiple icons much like one can choose their nickname for each server.

I love using it for chatting, it's the best place I've ever been too to find people just to talk and hang out, it makes it very easy to find someone to talk to or play games with by just finding a vc with people in It and hoping in. I just wish they would fix the disconnecting problems I've been having... Either, I hear nobody and I have to leave the vc/call and come back or nobody hears me and I have to for some reason unplug my headphones and plug it back in just to be heard....

Normally I would have given Discord a 5 Star Rating, but recently the app has been acting a bit strangely whenever I rotate my phone a bit. It will blank out the screen for a second or so and then be scrolled up an arbitrary amount upwards. Also the cropping on images is a little annoying. Other than that, Discord is basically my social lifeblood, making for a fantastic way to keep in contact with my friends.

Generally a very useful app. I've always loved discord and the features they've offered have always been very useful. I like specifically how in a server you can customize everything and have separate channels ect. There are a few bugs here and there but compared to Skype its much more reliable for gaming with large groups of people simultaneously.

This is very fun because you can make new friends and talk to them! I made 3 BEST friends, but I have other friends. I like how you can send pictures to a group or private chat. I ask my friends to show me some of their OCs and I draw them for my friends. One of my friends drew me my OC KittyMeow Sparkles. That's where my name came from!

I like this app. It makes you stay in touch with friends and you can meet new friends. Although I have a big complaint; the status feature. Discord always clears my status even tho I told it not to clear it at all. It's happened to my buddies too. I use it on my android phone all the time. You really need to fix this bug.

He entire Dev team is so friendly. Not just they're really inclusive warning messages and other things that the app shows you but the features of the application in itself. From receiving notifications and replying to them to the UI of the app. I love everything that they have been doing ever since I joined in. Don't worry about your account being stolen because the moment you set up your security on your account you should be good to go. Just don't do anything stupid

This is the best for people to get together and there's servers for everyone and a sweet spot for communities to get together. Has less bugs than most social apps and suppourt is great and when it started, it was just a place for gamers to get together but now its a whole lot more and actually i felt bad for such a great app be very underrated in the beginning but now the discord community is blooming.

It's a good and well orginized app. I'm used to the browzer version but was very easily able to adapt to this. The notification settings are very customizable which makes it very useful. Only issue I have is that your unsent messages get deleted very, very fast unlike in the browser version where they stay forever. I understand if this feature is just impossible to impliment on phones but it would be useful if the messages stayed even a little bit longer.

The app is a great alternative to the desktop version... But it's absurd that the video calls and streaming don't keep the phone's display turned on, and that the first complaint about this (and promised fix) dates back to 2017..... My phone is set to turn screen off after a few minutes and there is no way to keep it always on, sadly, due to Motorola's configs... I'd love to be able to watch stuff in bed, but sadly I'll have to leave that task to Youtube.

95% of the time, discord is an amazing app. I love being able to communicate with multiple people so easily, and the things you are able to do in servers, ranging from roles and streaming, is really fun! But sometimes there are bugs and glitches, causing it to be very slow! The audio in calls cuts in and out, streams might be delayed, messages get sent twice for some reason, etc. I still love discord, but please fix these problems!

hii this app is truly AMAZING. I've mainly had it for like 3 years I'M LOVING ITTT!! But I have this one issue that I hope can be fixed!!! So whenever I'm in a discord call, it suddenly goes silent.. Like what? Then I have to leave and rejoin..... I just don't know when it happens but its kinda annoying but I LOVE DISCORD OVERALL!! I hope you can fix this small tiny glitch!:)

I love this and use it all the time. I would like for the computer role selection for other members (a list where you pick the roles you want to give opposed to a pop-up that closes with 1 rank) But overall and in every detail I love this app. Tough as a european most people who use it cant really play games with me. But timezones cant be changed.

Half way through a voice call I have to leave the call and rejoin because my friends stop hearing me. Other times I stop hearing them and have to do the same. Also my friends say they hear my voice with very low volume while using a Bluetooth headset with mic. And if I plug earplugs with a wired mic the app doesn't use the wired mic, instead it uses the built in phone mic, which is ridiculous. A lot to improve!

This app is the best and most compact message app ever made, sorry for the 4/5 stars, the only reason I gave this app 4 stars is because I have a suggestion, what if we had multiple sounds we could assign to be played when a specific person enters a voice call? I know I seem like I'm taking this app for granted but I'm not, I appreciate the creation of it but this feature would be very much accepted by all users of discord. Keep the app cool and thanks for reading this

Works pretty well most of the time, but leaving the 'in game overlay' on while playing Battlefront II (2005) causes some sort of error that renders a big black box over the screen. Also, call quality can get pretty bad sometimes even with full bars. Otherwise it's a pretty simple and easy to use chatting app.

Definitely one of the best messaging apps I've ever downloaded. It beats messenger in my opinion in terms of quality, voice chat, and other features. I highly recommend this. Two things about the app, i hope it can let you send videos in mobile, and i hope the voice and video chats get fixed. Thats it.

Great app. However, on a chromebook or android phone, and overlay button for push to talk would be great. When doing anything outside of Discord, you need to switch back to the program to push to talk. When gaming, you will have to switch between the app you are using and discord every time you need to communicate with other plays/gm etc.

The app is nice for phone users, but the app for desktop, including the Google version are giving me a lot of lag especially when I am in a voice call or video call. That could me from my PC, but the platform facebook doesn't give me any performance slowdowns. So overall the only peoblem i have is when i play a game and am in voice/video call.

Beats Skype, TeamSpeak, and any other outdated software. Has power bots useful for servers and moderators. Voice chat is also much smoother as well as screenshare. You can even get super creative with your text with markdown. 10/10 Will always use. - edit: I just wish we had keyword notifications like on Skype, so we wouldn't miss certain conversations.

i rely on this platform every single day of the year to comnect with my friends from all over the world. servers are easy to set up and maintain. the interface is easy and the software is stable 99%of the time. there is a bug sometimes on pc where you wont be able to hear anyone in the call and they can hear you or vice versa. but a part from that this is an essential piece of software for any competitive gamer or media channel. thank's for the great free software guys for real. we needded it.

I think you should keep the last update because I it was running better and the voice chat doesn't lag , the new update isn't good , the layout is pretty bad and I can't find the people that I block and unblock them , and the voice chat is lagging Even if you used the push to talk , people can bearly hear me from the mic , also they still didn't add screenshare.

I love. A + . Five stars. Two thumbs up. I like the channels to sort your conversation topics within friend groups and good search features. They show custom statuses and you can make custom reaction emojis from any image. Decent safety and two factor compatible. Voice and video calls are decent, shows ping rates, and you can mute server members if they're afk... Lots of options and compatibility to automate with bots and code. And I love the brandingüñ§ Would love to see video overlay on Android

highly efficient interface for voice calls, IMs, screen sharing, gaming together & just all around staying connected. there's a bit of a learning curve to the interface, especially for those who've never used the PC app, but it's not a very steep curve and once one gets the hang of it, it's hard to beat. and alongside all that, the app is just fun! the developers clearly care about their users and want everyone to have a good time while on Discord.

Discord covers everything from the basics to very specific features for servers and does it well. Bothered by a small, negligable issue? Discord will fix it next patch. Then they will add a feature that you hadn't even thought of that makes using Discord even EASIER. The thought put into improving the platform is amazing. Perfect for all your needs.

Discord is the best chat app for gaming communities and other common interests. The mobile app is almost as fully featured as the desktop version and gets updates constantly to add new features and smooth out the experience. Oh, and it's free without ads. It's all supported by people like me who pay for silly cosmetics. 10/10.

Great gamer app. Im pretty sure it is used for more than just gaming but thats all i use it for. That way i can follow my factions in the games i play, also get updates on the server i play on for multi-player games, and to communitcate with the people i play games with. Great app to have and if your a gamer like me it is a must have for sure

I miss some of the features from the PC version - but only because the interface on mobile is different- most those features are still infact on the mobile build, with a friend's help i can find what im looking for. But as far as its intended use on my phone goes, its perfect. If ya never used the app on PC before then you shouldn't be as confused on mobile as i was because you wont be relearning the app you were already familar with. That aside, it does as its intended with great results. üëç

It's a great social messaging app for everyone, primarily gamers. They have many options and are continuing to set up more. However, with all social messaging apps, please be careful who you talk to and which servers you join. Additionally, be careful with your identity and privacy. I recommend this app for getting together with friends, family, colleagues even. Support them if you would like to, Nitro is nice, even if I can't afford it myself.

I'm a little bias cause I'm a hype squad member but it's a very functional and easy to use app, the servers are great for focused disscussion and group chats are easy to use, I highly recommend it to anyone Perfect to use for family chats, my family uses a server for keeping in touch, keeping lists, assigning chores, and all kids of things, it's not just for kids and fandoms!

There is no reason for any kind of nerd to not get this app. No matter what it is you like, you CAN find a highly interactible community for it, and even if you don't, you can find your friends and have a better "texting" application than actual SMS, not to mention that it's video calls are better than Skype or FaceTime or ESPECIALLY Zoom. This is the ultimate communication app. Download it.

Well organised and useful messaging website. Private messaging and messaging in groups, voice messaging for dm and groups, video messaging for private chat. Lots of emoticons+ you can make your own in groups. You can use nicknames, change your name colour and make chat rooms with sub sections. Easy to block people, difficult to get unwanted messages. My favourite messaging application!

Discord is pretty great! I love how many different communities there are to join. It's very easy to stay connected with friends and family. I primarily use this app to stay in touch with my long distance boyfriend so I'm real happy. The only con is, that sharing screens to watch movies together is a pain so we have to switch to Skype which is only marginally better.

Best private and general messenging service available. Me and my husband double checked privacy statement. They basicly say they would only release information with a warrarnt (propper channels). Nothing is tracked or sold like fb either! And i love the ananomynity. Its designed for gamers. You cqn always change your name or make a new account. Join or leave a gaming community with no issues! This is how internet messenging should be.

I've been using discord for such a long time and I think discord is literally the best app in use for texting your friends and etc, could even be used for RP servers! It's a pretty good app and I'd recommend it to most people who like server stuff, and plus you can even use it to video share while quarantine or voice chat! A few years ago I found discord and I NEVER regret downloading it, honestly I have a lot of words how to describe how good it is. The video quality is great as well, download

Best app for group chats, communicating with friends, working with your team, etc. SUPER user friendly, very straight forward interface. Best emojis. If you can think of a feature it should have but doesn't; it's probably in the next update. Love that its also available on desktop or just a web browser and everything syncs. 10/10 would reccomend to all my friends
