Amazing system, been using for years for gaming, now is a life-saver during the times of social distancing. Simple to use but with some great little concepts in there - the bots alone are enough to keep my brand loyalty. Had a couple of issues in the 2+ years I've been using it, always fixed swiftly. Highly recommended.

Been using discord for a few years now , at this point I think the entire world knows about it and what it meant to be used for. That's an amazing program that is the leader of all social software and website options , it offers everything for free and provide the best experience for the user , I highly recommend for anyone to use it as a daily life program. ‚ô°

I love this chat room. It's the most well built chat I've seen in a while, and their dev team us amazing. The chat function is decent as well. It allows me to physically talk to my friends who aren't stateside, and that's something I thought I'd never see in my lifetime. I would highly reccomend Discord to anyone.

The best chatting app. Means when I'm out and about I can still be part of the action in my friends voice channels. Helps me keep up to date with what's happening in the gaming world thanks to all the different servers and channels you can join. Great app, trying to get my offline friends to convert from WhatsApp.

This is the greatest app and website/PC app for talking with your teammates, friends, classmates and teacher's. (during covid) I highly recommend this app to anyone who wants to do the above! I use this app daily to speak with friends and teammates, as well as keep up to date on my favorite streamers and YouTubers, while interacting with them live on their custom made servers. This app allows awesome server and user customization, never seen before in other communication apps. I highly recommend

Best UI in a chat app. Speaks wonders when every friend I get into it can immediately figure it out and has good things to say about it. Also has the best video and stream quality I've seen from anything similar. Friends and I use it to share video or games all the time. It's great for any kind of community you can imagine!

Whenever on call, everyone in the voice server goes silent and then we can't hear me. I have to jump out and jump back in which might persist this over and over again. It's timed randomly when it happens and honestly aggravates gameplay when trying to communicate to team. Also notifications keep playing up like I receive or don't receive any never know when it happens.

Been using discord for a few years now and it rarely has randomly dropped calls or poor quality of calls. I can talk to people anywhere in the world and not have issues with quality, be it a friend in America, New Zealand or Sweden. Discord doesn't have ads or any secret monetization, just nitro if you want to be able to use emotes from any server anywhere else. The only complaint I have is that DMs and @s don't always generate a notification.

Fantastic messaging app which is more suited for gamers, since it's features include but not limited to: font customisable, role designation and permissions, different bots with functions, voice channels as well as different channels with different permissions. Developers are also always improving the app, reportedly based on users' feedback and suggestions.

Great way to chat with people across the world with similar interests to myself as well as keep in touch with friends, the party chat system also helps when whatever particular game system we're playing is having a few issues with it's own chat systems. Even used it to play a dnd campaign with people across the globe.

Discord is a life-changer, despite it's few quirks and some issues with voice or video chat, it is incredibly reliable and amazing to use. Yes, IRC users might not change their mind but for everyone else? It's great, and I personally prefer it over Slack for just how great the UX is and it's sheer amount of customization it comes with, my addiction to it knows no bounds and it has even helped me beyond gaming.

It's just objectively great. Nothing of Discord's size and quality gets away without some controvercy, and Discord has very little, which actually means you can enjoy it for said size and quality, and let me tell you, it's huge. Anyone can make as many servers as they want, split it up as much as they want, play with a litteny of features that work 99% of the time every time, which you just don't see. For whatever reason you might want an app like this, Discord is a fantastic go-to option.

Overall, this app runs smoothly. Technical problems are always addressed and resolved in a timely manner. The communities you find on it is vast and engaging. Although, it can be confusing when you first use it, taking a little time getting familiar with the features will go a long way in enjoy the app fully.

Discord is actually insane. I can talk with my friends for free and create servers which can respond to commands with a custom bot! I highly recommend this for gamers and anyone who just wants to keep in touch with a close friend or relative! It would be good if they could increase the file upload limit to friends and or DMs but keep it at 8mb for servers. Overall solid app that works through almost any device!

Perhaps the best app for gaming communities. Not only gamers but for anyone who wants to hang out with friends, with features such as voice chat and screen sharing. However, one thing to note is that emoji panel is buggy, it mostly lags out when you try to open it. I have checked this thing on multiple smartphones, and the problem persists. I hope it will be fixed.

It is really good at what it is supposed to be. Yes, I met idiots and jerks on it, but that shouldn't affect my rating on the app itself. It is more then just a combination app and can be used from a variety of purposes, like roleplay and even DnD. There is plenty more to also do with it. I would highly recommend it.

Discord is great but lacks some of the communication filters that teamspeak offers, such as group binds so you can make user groups to speak to specifically. I also miss the ability to place a phantom in another channel to listen in, while voice chatting elsewhere that Ventrilo offered. There are numerous wonderful features for running your own server, and screen streaming. Discords capabilities negate the need for your group to have a website for any reason. Try karaoke, or watch movies

It's a messaging app, group chats and @ are useful obviously, it just has a huge issue where I'm not always notified someone messages me. Edit: forgot about screenshare issues, just doesn't really work. No audio or just not working at all. Just wanted to flex my saber skills but alas

Excellent service. The drop in feature is particularly handy as our previous program required the host to invite people every time. Runs well with very rare outages which are typically resolved promptly. Only niggle is the small file size for transfer, to increase it you have to pay which you didn't on my previous software choice. All in all an excellent service.

Idk man like I've been asked to review every single app I've ever downloaded and many are 5 stars to me but I don't rate it. Discord is like 5 stars + must tell ppl about it. I really enjoy the work the developers are constantly putting in. Thank you!!!!!!!

The app is really useful for connecting with friends, and I rarely have any issues with the app; however, there is a bug where I'll be talking with friends through a voice chat in our server and the audio will just cut out. I know how to fix this periodically by leaving then rejoining the voice chat, however this shouldn't happen to begin with. This is a reoccuring bug, though I don't know how it happens. I usually am on WIFI when this happens. I hope this helps to get this fixed.

Great app! I typically use it for gaming and as a place for keeping in touch with friends. It has definitely been useful over the past few months. My only complaint is that you can't post videos in the standard version (apparently you only can with Nitro), I would love to see the ability to post short clips that i've made.

Absolutely brilliant, and easy and free to use. I love that you can get so many people on a call. We've had over 30 on a call before, it's amazing. My only flaw would be when it struggles to connect (but I think that's more of my WiFi being terrible, which it usually is) or if the servers go down, but understandably that can't be helped, and is always fixed quickly afterwards. Overall, a great app, easy to use, no ads, you get many people on call, completely free - what more could you want?

Great to chat with friends all over the world! It even have a built in translator that make it easy to talk in different languages. So many different ways to interact with your friends, I really sound like a commercial lol but I really love this app!!! Support is always helpful and generally kind but efficient.

Been using Discord for 5 years, always been a reliable way to stay in contact with my friends and people I meet in games. Everything else about Discord is just perfect. However I have really struggled with getting the voice side of Discord working. Probably doing something wrong but it doesn't seem like it should be this hard

Some or most times discord via the app does crash here and there & it has happened pretty frequently, which is very irritating to deal with especially when I'm in a vc or a call with someone. However, I'm throughly enjoying all of the newly updated things within the app especially the vc overlay to let one know who is clearly talking & of course I will continue to use discord for as long as that may be.

At first it was a little confusing to understand but it barely took time to get a hold of it. Really useful for gaming and chatting to friends So many servers on anything you can think (to join a server go to Google and search *example* Minecraft Discord servers) The use of screen share on pc is very handy and has pretty good quality Only bad thing is the discord nitro Overpriced and I don't see any use of buying it Apart from that great app

Great chat program combining the best of Skype, Steam Community and classics like AIM and MSN with the best of modern messenger apps. Plus, the easy creation and sharing of communities makes it feel like a strong modern iteration of classic chats and forums, while supplying superior voice chat and screen sharing capabilities. My one stop for chatting for quite awhile now.

I never have a problem with this app it's super nice to use to keep in touch with all my racing buddies. The communities I can keep up with using Discord it's really fun and easy to use. Except for sometimes the UI can be a little weird but I'm still going to give it five stars because I really really like this app.

Well designed intuitive interface. Very effective for gaming or multi person chatting. Very smooth operation in multi-person video amd voice call. Allows unique user server set ups like a digital Bullpen. Tons of user customization and intagration with other Soft wear Clients. Takes up minimal processing power. All of this is offered for free. The subscription servixe or Nitro service is optional enabling even more control via customization and analyics for your server and networks. Recomended!!

Discord is honestly the most effective chat interface I've ever used and it's so easy to navigate. I see everywhere on tons of servers across the globe the opportunities discord opened up for them. It's a very unique experience and very useful to chat to other gamers on cross platform games with their amazing voice and video chat! Great job and a well earned 5 star from me ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ

Great app, you don't even have to play games to get use out of this app. A little complicated to use when you 1st start but, after a bit of searching through everything it becomes really easy to use. You can voice call, video chat, or just message another person. If you join a discord group I suggest editing what notifications you get. If there are a lot of people in the discord group your phone will continue to get notifications.

This is the neatest app I hav ever used. Ive ised it on the pc since 2016, and have made and enriched many friendships accrost the platform. Its not just for games, its also a wonderfully endearing way to keep in touch. Customizing your avatar anf changing your display name is easy, and it was ome of the first platforms to be so user friendly. Wumpus is great- although I don't see them much- the platform has humor and in general has the big cute. Please install this platform, its uniquely fine

Discord is like Skype and reddit combined. Imagine Subreddits but you can have your own private ones where you can do and say what you want. Not only that but you can also have voice chats in the server, which is pretty epic. Only bad thing about discord is if you use light theme, but dark theme is the default so your eyes will be fine.

Best community and interpersonal communication application of all time. No close second. If you're looking to create a place for fans, friends, or even communication within a workplace team; this is the application to use. The desktop experience is top tier, with any feature loss on mobile being completely justified and understandable due to the change in platform. Mobile app is still seamless, smooth, and with more than enough functionality to manage communication on the go.

I've used this app for almost two years now, and while a few of the changes have been a bit odd, it remains the best text and voice chat app I have personally used. My only real complaint is the inability to move channels around on my servers while on mobile. Otherwise, I recommend it highly to all my friends!

Discord is hecking AWESOME. It's a simple app that helped me keep in contact with friends from far away. It's suitable for children because ...weird people.. can't access their account without a tag&username or without that user's consent(still keep an eye out for who your kid's talking to). Real easy to use, and sometimes it may be laggy but it offers so much, so it's understandable. Perfect for gamers, just heckin easy 20/10

I've been using Discord for years to chat with friends and join groups to discuss common interests. Its voice chat isn't the best in my experience, but it excels as a versatile messaging app that can be used on mobile, computer, and in browser. It works well for streaming games to friends as well.

Have been a user of both this and the desktop version of discord, will say foremost is the user experience is amazing and very intuitive from joining other user created servers to creating your own and forming bonds with groups of people, always adding new features monthly-yearly and building on the original foundations of voice communication, a must have for anyone wanting to find online communities.

The app for the most part is great. I have two complaints. 1. During a group voice chat it happens a lot where I can't hear anyone and then I have to hang up and connect to the call again to hear everyone. this happens to other users. 2. When I am watching a Stream I cant l dont have a quality option to change to 480p 720p. Why? I hope they continue to improve the streaming service.

The best platform to use to talk with friends online. Really good for gaming itself, I clearly love the styling of it. Has support from many websites and open code community who work on bots which do many things such as playing desired music or moderation on channel. Discord is great even tho it has some downtimes. Would be 5 if the notifications were not broken on mobile phones since a patch or two. Plox fix it asap =)

It's been a great experience over the last couple of years. Just wish a update would go out that would give us chat heads (similar to Facebook Messenger) so when I'm playing a mobile game with members of my guild I don't have to either have another device or switch to the discord app and back. Sometimes my games crash when that happens.

One of the best apps I've ever used! It has its bugs at times, but it allows so much for what it is. Video streaming, chat channels, voice channels, great quality on all of them. If you love emotes, this platform is great even if it takes 5$ a month to use them in any server.

Very well setup for those who are part of gaming communities. Quality of voice calls will obviously depend on region, but having used this in multiple Provinces (Canada) and multiple states, I can confirm the overall voice chat quality is comparable if not slightly higher than Zoom and Skype. I cannot speak for video chatting, so if that's what you're looking for, you'll have to see another reviewer.

I use it on mobile to chat with pc friends while playing on xbox. Way better than xbox party chat. Mostly works great. Only problem I have is randomly losing audio while connected to a voice chat room. Being able to individualy adjust others voice volumes while chatting is the most wonderful feature and also why I give 4 stars. The random audio issue is what is keeping it from the elusive 5th star.

This is a wonderful app that has somehow gotten better!! Discord has always been easy to use and customize, but has recently undergone changes to help hone the customer's experience. Whether you are gaming with friends or conferencing with colleagues, discord has the tools to make it simple and easy!

I use Discord extensively, almost every day. It's hard to believe something this good is free. It's not quite perfect, though. I would find it easy to recommend if it had end to end encryption, or if you could link invite people to calls rather than servers. Its reliability is also lower than I'd like (99% instead of 99.99% uptime) Overall, I get great use out of it both for meetings and gaming voice chat. I highly recommend it!

I use this application a lot while I'm on the go. I have used it for our d&d groups, raids in WoW, all sorts of games. I love the ptt options when I'm not at the computer. I do wish I could get better at getting some notifications over others. Ei whispers or private messages, my phone doesnt alert me. That's my only comment that may be iffy. I love it other than that!

I've used discord more or less every day since late 2017. I have no plan of abandoning it any time soon. However there are a couple features that are not possible on mobile that are pretty essential. Like there being no way to add a spoiler warning to an image on mobile. Other than that though I love it 100%

This is one of the best apps you can get as of right now and ever. It's a great way to make friends that also have similar interests as you. It's simple to make a server for your friends. There are also several ways of interaction. You can text your messages, speak with people in a voice chat, or (if you're personal preference is ok with it) an NSFW can be put on certain areas. Having too much trouble because the chat is going too fast? Try slowmode! It's the best social media app you there!

Discord has always been amazing and it keeps on improving. I have used it almost every day on PC and mobile since release for gaming voice, news, keeping in touch with friends, running school clubs, and most recently video calling. Honestly this is my single favorite piece of software of all time. This review is truly my honest opinion and nobody paid me to say these things. If you want a way to connect with gamers, colleagues, club members, friends or family, this is the way to go.

I've been using discord for a few years now, and they are amazing. From the two simple yet easy to read themes (plus an extra one if you know the secret), to the ease of being able to change usernames and have different nicknames for different servers, they are a great platform. Even if you don't purchase nitro, you aren't punished, and I can't remember the last time, if ever, I've seen an ad here. The block function is great as you don't have to leave mutual servers, but you can be shielded. 5*

Have yet to completely explore the application the few years of use it has gotten has been quite enjoyable. Going to agree with black willow here and restate that it is truly incredible that it is able to be used free of charge. The ability to have group conversations with family and friends all over the world, share photos, stream videos, makes a person feel a sense of connection in times of isolation. Thank's Discord team!

Great platform for communities of all types, and the developers are making it better every month. Video is better than Skype or Zoom, and the voice chat has always been really clear. In fact I prefer it while gaming with friends over the in game voice features of most games. Best of all, it is all free with no ads whether you're joining a server or creating your own community. Would give 6 stars if I could.

Very useful app for communication both text and voice. It's free to use which is amazing and is highly versatile and allows for PC users to share their screens, which can be viewed on mobile. Video sharing is also available. You can also file share and create various servers for different groups

I have been using Discord since it first came out. Coming from Skype, it was different at the same time a bit better. Then they added screen-sharing and video calls. I won't lie, when they say 'a voice chat created by gamers for gamers' they weren't kidding. If you need it for a voice or anything like that, you can depend on it's smooth connection.

It's a great app to use for friends and making new friends! Fun servers and chats. Lots of options. However, I've had to uninstall and install this app 6 times in the past few days... I use it on a phone. I'll go to see my profile or friend's list and then it'll only show 3 options? It won't let me change my status or profile (the buttons for it won't show up). I download it and then it'll show up, but then once I click on it again after x'ing it out, it does it all over again. Help please.

One of my preferred ways of communicating with people. I don't even play videogames as much but still use the app because of how common it is for people to use. It's layout reminds me of slack and it's easy to use and get the hang of. Makes organizing events, clubs, and talking to friends more convenient

Lately they made some major changes, which improved the whole service of discord itself. Voice messages would be a nice option. I also like the integrated code highlighting functionality. In our company, we are trying to implement something different than discord, but we always get back to it xD

Discord is a great app that has many useful chat and call features to connect users from many regions. I like all the things that discord has in store. However, discord has some connection problems a lot of the time. For example, sometimes images don't load (even though I have good wifi) and messages are very slow to send. In come cases, I can't even log on. Would appreciate if this would be fixed. Thanks!

To start, think of it as Skype for gamers. After that, it's solo much more. Very easy to set up and customize a server for you and your friends/raid, which you can invite them with a quick 2 clicks. Lots of public servers out there that's easy to find with the browse button for like-minded groups of people looking to meet new people. And the couple of times I sent a message to the system I got a human response that wasn't afraid to joke around a bit and that felt pretty good.

If we're talking about the UI and overall functionality, I think it's great. My only problem is the fact that, (and this is probably an unpopular opinion) the toxicity of what appears to be many of the communities. It almost comes off as an 18+ site given the amount of NSFW content so many servers have. I don't believe it's entirely discord fault, but if they believe a warning on age requirements is going to help... well, it's not. I know what I'm saying wont change anything, but oh well.

Smooth, fast and easy to handle. Makes communicating with your buds whilst playing games, or whatever else you choose to do, clear and quick with practically no lag in sound. For reference I'm in Japan and use this app to communicate with my brother back in New England. There's a reason why basically all streamers use this platform, it's good and works phenomenally.

Discord is awesome for communicating with friends while playing games, that's what it's known for. One of the best features is being able to create groups to organize and keep track of distinct friend groups. Recently I've also discovered that it's even more reliable than group texting, and use it for more and more general communications. Thank you Discord developer team for making such a useful and awesome app!

This is a good and I use it almost every day but the recent update causes problems. It was very useful being able to see who was talking while scrolling through chat. I am not a big fan of the green voice connected bar on the top of the screen. Every so often the people in a call won't be able to hear me and I won't be able hear them which is pretty annoying. Sometimes if I try to go on a different app while in a call it will randomly turn my screen black and won't allow me to do anything.

There are no lags, the latency is pretty low and it has an extensive Set of Features that you can make use of. Sometimes when I call people on the other side of the globe audio and video may stop randomly but since that happens only on few occasions and performance, latency and audio and video quality are really good, I guess you can confidently overlook that.

It's a great app in just about every way it's my favorite app currently the only problem right now is the scam bots but other than that I say this is the best app for just getting to know people or finding new friends and people to talk to. This is the app I'm on most so it's obviously my favorite app I'd rate it 5 stars anytime!

This app is great, but recently when I got my new phone (Galaxy S10), when I call my friends, after a while we have to redo the call because eventually my voice starts sounding robotic to them. This seems like a device specific issue, but I'm not too sure. I have very good wifi. Also, my mobile data is very good aswell. So idk why this happens. Anyways, I hope you guys fix this. Its a bit snnoying having to hang up and redo a call because they can't hear me properly.

I used to love discord, But all these recent new updates for the past couple months made the app problematic. It would cut the audio every 10-20 minutes and if I'm looking at someone's stream it cuts the audio every 5-10 minutes. And My friends have the same problems on their devices, so it's not only me, and me and my friends were thinking about moving to something else so then we don't have to worry about audio issues anymore?

This is the one of the best apps to communicate with friends or communities you decide to make if you're a streamer, creator, or just a dude who wants to have a virtual hangout spot with friends. So much fun. Little to no supervision like Reddit. So you can say and do as you please without any consequence of "you can't post for the next ten minutes".

I absolutely love this app. I spend almost all my time talking to kind people and finding games play with other great people. And even though there are bot glitches, they shouldn't get in the way of things. But even though I emailed the devs asking a question that I needed clarification, they haven't responded to me in 4 days. Overall, this amazing addictive app received 4 stars!

The best way to talk to friends. You can type, voice chat, send pictures and emojis, and screen share video and audio at excellent quality; and it's all free! Very rarely has any server issues. It's always being updated with new features and fixes and in my opinion it's the best way to talk to your gaming community friends. Would recommend.

Discord is such an amazing and free communication. It was originally designed with people who play games in mind, but over the past few major updates it has become very streamlined! I personally use it daily because it let's me connect with everyone I want to talk to from friends to strangers.

Easily the best modern app for 1-on-1 or group messaging. Use it for personal, use it for a community, use it for business. I do all three and this app has never let me down. It takes Skype or Zoom, and blows them out of the water. If there's a feature you want that they don't have, write them about it and they are likely to add it. Best app out there, listens and delivers for it's users. The only thing I could ask for is a separate business version of the app for professional settings.

For those who have never used Discord, it's a fantastic way to connect with people through text or over video, either one-on-one or dozens at a time. And best of all, it's totally free. You can pay for extras like being able to use server-specific emojis everywhere, but this is completely unnecessary to have a great experience. For those who use the desktop version, I'd argue the app is better, which a sign of good design on the devs' part. Kudos!

It is the best voice/video/chatting service on the market. If you want to just call a friend, it's easy. If you want to create an entire community around that thing you love and easily be able to share pictures, it's easy. If you use anything else and have had frustrations with them, try discord. It's free.

Decades ago IRC was the only way to chat, Discord takes IRC and gives it a full comprehensive overhaul with all the features a modern community would expect. Not just server based communication but a seamless voice and video experience. It feels wrong to refer to Discord as a chat client as it does so much more in much better ways, with third party bots enhancing that experience ever further.

Fun! I have made some very close friends, especially in this new time of a critical pandemic. It has been nice to have Discord as an outlet while being in a lockdown situation. People from all over the world were affected, but we have been able to reach out and connect with those friends and spend time together to lift each other in the time of need.

I love Discord! It's very fun to use and can be used for more than just gaming. It can be used professionally as well! The only complaints I really have is the quality I have for voice chatting and streaming seems to lag a lot. I can't say if it's entirely me! So take that with a grain of salt. The other thing is the hackers that go around and sex bots. It isn't huge problem though, the developers have really cracked down on it! The developers have done so much and the app only gets better.

Overall, good app. I've been using this for years now on both phone and desktop version and it's pretty good. It's great for gaming, but it can also be used for just chatting. The only downsides are probably the somewhat buggy voice chats and the file size limits. Other than that, this is probably the best app out there for messaging and voice calls, especially with large numbers of people.

Discord is hands down the best VOIP and text chat service on the market. Built for gamers from the ground up, they have not strayed from their target audience despite the wider potential market for their product. Downtime is extremely rare, and when it does occur, the problem is fixed very quickly and Discord provides updates on fix status every few minutes. And honestly, it's worth getting just to read the hilarious patch notes. There is no other app for which I can't wait to read patch notes.

I have worked with many chat, voice and video communication applications and services both professionally and casually. Discord is seamless, secure, easy to operate and incredibly reliable. I haven't found any services that are comparable, the free services have been better than any business applications i use. Love you Discord üíú

I use it every day to talk to my friends and communicate while playing games. Sometimes there are some issues with live streaming, but we don't mind. You can be a part of so many different groups and keep them relatively organized. The update notes they give are simplified for regular non-computer folk to understand, so everyone knows what's going on. It's also pretty easy to learn, despite the large amount of features they have.

Discord is the best! The best VoIP I have ever used. Built in streaming works on both Mobile and Desktop versions. I can watch my brothers game from bed when I am feeling sick! I am trying to convince all the family members to use it instead of Facebook and other apps. My parents figured it out and enjoyed a nice of Streaming Cats and Shittalking .

I have a problem with it.And the problem is this that a year ago I joined discord but due to some personal problem I had to delete it.But now I downloaded Discord again.And I clicked 'Register'.But when I put my e-mail address it said "E-mail already registered". So I clicked 'Login' and put my e-mail and password.And then I clicked on 'Verify'.But it said "New login location detected, please check your e-mail." This was my mistake but now how to solve it?

Easy and fun way to connect with others, in various ways. Plus, they seem to be respectful to each server's autonomy. I haven't noticed or heard of them doing any censoring which is great. At least so far. And that's great. And the app works great. I think the only thing I would change is to be able to see who up voted emoticons. Very very good app. It's very easy to keep servers organized, and it's very aesthetically pleasing. The voice and video chats are pretty good, although my boyfriend's mobile cam is very laggy over discord for some reason and we cannot find a way to fix it. His camera on his computer works great but we would both like it if the mobile camera wasnt laggy. Other than that, great app!

I honestly dont know what I would do without Discord. I used to use TS3 and Skype, but Discord is a staple in my life now. The only thing I'd like to see is more tools for text editing and maybe more options for bot development. I've seen a lot of cool things built, and do build my own bots, but just a few more tools to be able to get EXACTLY what I want would be great. For example, being able to directly color and style text, or utilize HTML markup for the welcome channel would be a godsend.

No calls ever dropped and easy to navigate/use. I've only had good experiences with Discord. I love getting together with friends on here and chatting. The voice chat feature is great and convenient as a mom and doesn't take up as much battery power as Facebook messenger. I have Discord installed on mobile and my computer.

Awesome app, although I have had some problems with voice chat on the mobile app. Sometimes when I'm in a voice chat, the call gets muted. It does not appear to be muted, but I can't hear anything, and people in the voice channel cannot hear me either. So I am forced to exit the voice channel and enter again which is very annoying when this happens during a gameplay voice chat.

I've honestly used this app for years and never thought of rating it. There are some moments were it says "connecting" and I can't send messages as quick as usual, but those spurs usually last for around 5 minutes and in the last six years I've used this app, that's probably happened about a dozen times (which is great). I highly recommend this app.

It's a great adaptation to the (superior) desktop app. Although not as good it does do its job and does it well, coming from a phone app standpoint. If you don't have a Computer/Laptop or are away and have no access to it, this actually does a great job to fill that gap. Great audio quality, some features unavailable but the phone version is at its strongest as a social app, mainly messages and voicechat.

This app is one of the best, if not the best. However, my only complaint and reason why I dropped a star is while on Voice Chat quite often does people's voices randomly drop out and no one can hear that person. It doesn't matter how many peole are in the VC. Otherwise an amazing app.

Typically thought of as an app used by gamers, Discord is not only that but a great app for communication of all sorts. Group message boards, organization, and coordination are all very easily done with Discord. The mobile app has gotten its fair share of attention from the developers and everything is streamlined and easy to use without compromising function. My only complaint is the character limit (2000) for text posts. This should either not exist, or else it should be something adjustable.

It works. Sometimes. Most of the time the app works perfectly and I wouldn't replace it for another alternative. However sometimes the app just randomly stops sharing screen and the audio becomes muted while other people can hear you. This is easily fixed by e restart but that's not the point I'm trying to make. As the biggest voice app amongst "gamers" I expected more.

Discord is great, I've been using discord for almost 4 years now and it has always been amazing to use. By far the best app for communication, and the streaming function on desktop is amazing! Another thing I really like is that people on mobile and desktop can still call each other and enjoy themselves.

So I use this app atleast 3 times a week and it is amazing it never glitches and the quality i get using this app I couldn't find with anyone else .. ( believe me I have looked around just to see üëÄ) I am totally satisfied with how it works and how easy it is to setup from the get go ... we use it mostly for rpg on the occasion we use it to get together and talk with our family across the pond . both ways are clear no static and no loss of communication by either party member. Sincerely Slpw

I've been using Discord as my primary means of communications for social and gaming purposes for the better part of a year now. Beyond that, I've been on discord since mid 2018 and a Nitro subscriber since June 2019. I have to say, when it comes to audio quality, streaming for your friends, video chat, ease of use/access, user interface quality, etc. Very few services are as well curated as Discord is. If you aren't already on Discord (for whatever reason) and are considering it, go for it.

Great with minor hiccups. I've really only experienced problems with the app when reconnecting to a voice call/server. Sometimes if the connection drops momentarily it will start playing audio back through the phone speakers instead of the headphones. Other than that, its great for keeping up with friends online.

I do wish the standard character limit was raised. I think it should be infinite. Not sure why it isn't. Another thing is the image send limit, wish it was over 10. One last thing, I do wish the size limit would be increased to 10 mbs. Nitro can fix this but it would just be more generous. The app is great. Everything I listed aren't pain points, rather just tiny betterments I think would make the standard experience a bit better. Or maybe add it to discord nitro.

I'm not giving 5 stars just because I met my husband on Discord but... well I kinda am üòÇ All jokes aside, Discord is a great place to socialize as a gamer (or as a non-gamer as well). You'll have a more positive experience than on any other social platform in my opinion. If you're going to be a very active member, you can subscribe to get more features. All in all an awesome place to get to know new people or to keep up with friends online.

Amazing app, I use it daily and have no complaints at all, voice quality is great and there are seldom connectivity issues (and when there are they are easily fixed). It is a great platform for gaming with friends, just hanging out and community building. Lastly I've been using it even more lately because of the corona situation and I've gotten many friends to use the app who are not accustomed to use computer programs a lot, but due to the great interface they all often use and enjoy the app!

Best social media app I've ever used so far, (gotta love the funny and casual update notes) You can voice/video call, stream your game, share your screen and you can use dozens of free bots to make your experience more fun(It's like adding mods to Minecraft ;>) The only downside is the file size limit, would be cool if they could increase it in the future. Anyways, I've been using Discord for over 2 years and I absolutely love it, keep bringing more awesome updates.

It's Discord. Everything you would expect of Discord just in mobile form. Excellent audio quality, little to no latency, all the settings you'll ever need, great optimization, easy to use. As far as mobile ports go, this was done great. Plus, it's Discord, I mean come on, you know it's at least decent without even having to read this review.

Amazing program on desktop and mobile. An ever evolving platform that constantly adds new features and improves upon existing ones. There are very few developers out there that listen to the feedback of their users like these guys. It was made as a gaming platform, but can be used for so much more.

An all round solid app, great for group calls, video calls, streaming, screen sharing, etc. Best thing is that even though it's free, there are no ads and it's far better than Skype for calls. There are a few occasional bugs (like sound suddenly vanishing from a stream) that pop up here and there, but they are usually fixed in a few days.

I've been using Discord for many years now, and I must admit it is the best platform for communication. What I love the most is the ability to add custom emotes (thank you so much for this) and the ability to change server location in a matter of milliseconds. All this makes the experience extremely fluid and enjoyable. Are there any negative sides? Honestly, I can't think of any. The addition of love streaming directly to voice channels made this app absolutely complete. 11/10

I love this! It is a great app for gamers/nerds. It is awesome to use while you are playing a mobile game! It does cut out 1 or 2 times in a 1 hour call bit that's no problem. I love how you can join servers and chat through there. Overall this is a great app and you should download it!

Most features work fine and I have no trouble with them. However the custom status feature (specifically on mobile, PC is fine) is awful. My custom status is cleared at random despite setting it to "don't clear." I can't maintain my status, my friends tell me my status disappears for them all the time, and it seems to decide when it wants to show up again at random.

AMAZING app for chatting. It can be a bit glitchy at times, but the updates have been good, and the overall user experience is very good as well. I do wish they would change some things, like the fact you can only join 100 servers at a time, and also the fact you can't be notified when someone only mentions you and no one else in the server. But other then that the app works great, is fast, has no ads, and is better then many other chatting apps. I highly recommend this. Happy chatting üôÇ

Recently the app stopped working with my bluetooth headset. I can hear friends talking in calls, but it will not allow me to talk. It is not a problem with the headset itself, as I've done testing with other apps and it works just fine everywhere but here. The game may be hard to play at first, but it gets easier once you fully understand the mechanics. The gacha is pretty much a love and hate relationship, the characters as a bait to play, but the plotline really balances things out. The devs are pretty much generous with the stuffs needed, but I'm really tired of wasting 1k sanity for farming everyday lol. Anyways, I really like the interface and the features of the game. Hoping that the global would catch up soon with the CN ver soon!

Great app and all been using it for 3 years and the constant improvement is really nice to see, with that said the channel and members list drawers open way too easily at the slightest swipe and it gets annoying and sometimes the custom status doesn't show on my profile when I re-open the app after a bit, even though my status is online and I'm connected. Anyway, didn't mean to make it seem like just a list of complaints, I really do enjoy this app, and want to see it grow, keep up the good work

Being a beta tester for Discord when it first came into being, the app has come a long, long way from where it started years ago. I never thought it would be used on the phone, let alone be a big part in this pandemic going on but this app is the greatest. I won't use anything else when it comes to an instant message system.

Great app, reasonably easy to use. Handy for notifications when I'm out and about to keep updated with any game changes. Video call function works well. The only thing that would improve it would be having the functionality to use GIFs; it's available on the computer version bit doesn't seem to be on the app. Other than that, very happy and would recommend.

This app is awesome for quarentine and just chatting, although you might want to rethink the mobile If you want a good sound. So unless you can afford a three hundred dollar headset to plug into the phone (most of us can't), don't expect good sound. But overall a great app!

It provides an easy way to connect and discuss with my fellow team mates on a project, all the topics that we care to speak about. It has voice calls and chat access features that are simple and friendly to use. Overall a great app and keep up the nice work Discord Development Team!

it used to be really great but there has been a bug i think? that currently prevents me from hearing anybody and nobody could hear me either.. it usually gets fixed by itself after 15-30 minutes, i've tried reconnecting, restarting my phone, changing to another device, reinstalling the app, changing servers, changing settings, nothing works all i can do is to wait, i have tried to call on telegram and it works perfectly fine but not on discord.. please help I'm giving up on you!!!

The app has everything the PC program does. Discord is a great service, but I'm having an issue. My calls go through and my friends say it sounds like I'm in a hurricane. When I open a call I have to switch from "speaker" to "phone" to stop this. Then they say it's like listening to me on mute. I have a Google Pixel 4xl and don't have any issues with my microphone on cellular calls. I've tried messing with the options and haven't found a solid fix.

Discord is a great app to use to connect with friends and meet other people with the same intrest as you but I have issues with calling. Although I'm connected to my internet it still tells me that the connection to the call is bad even though I have all of my apps closed besides discord. Also, sometimes the person on the other end starts lagging. Discord has been lagging more often then usual, I hope you guys can fix these bugs.

The app used to be ok. Nowadays it's not good 1. Unless, you are pro-user, many of the addtional emoji's are darkened and take space, waste resources but cannot be used. 2. The prev update enlarged the server status drawer to the right. It takes an entire screen to show members. Before, it took less than 1/2 & you could see the chat screen for the current channel. Edit: I had a new suggestion. If the pics could be darker in night mode. Would be great. I get blinded by white in dark mode.

So it's been almost two months since the UI update. I've gotten used to the new UI and now it doesn't bother me as much as it used to. Custom Role colors have finally hit mobile, which I'm excited about! Now I can make my server look cooler!!! If you guys are able to try and apply the Twemoji to nicknames, channel names, and server names (or wherever else it isn't working) that would be splendid!

I love this application. I use it to talk to buy Dungeons & Dragons group. We don't even have to use voice call we can text if we want to. There are a lot of choices in this application and I highly suggest it. Discord if you are reading this give me headpats for being good boy.

Best chat, voip, foip and screen share/streaming app out there both on Android and Windows platforms. Especially if you are into gaming. Then there is no contest - this is what you need. Plus, servers all run on hamster wheels so you know they'll still keep going, even in case of an apocalypse. ;)

90% of the time, it's great. Text operations are smooth and almost everything I could want. Voice is where my opinion wanes--on desktop, far less likely to cut out spoken audio, but it still occasionally happens. From mobile, it's almost indecipherable at times.

Definately a good app. If for whatever reason I'm playing a game that makes ALT+TAB not an option, Star Citizen, then it updates with what im being sent instantly between app on desktop and phone. The only "gripe" I would have is that it seems to jump in and out of connection a lot unless you're on wi-fi.

Best social platform. I joined in 2016 for the gaming features, and today I use it to talk to my best friends, communities, games, and even classmates around the world. Discord also has exceptional staff members that have been listening to their users and optimizing the platform over and over for our experience. Thank you for all you've done for us, especially during these hard times.

I absolutely love Discord!! For a little over a year now, I have been using it. It was a way to contact my friends from school in an easy way, and I've been able to be in groups of people that share my interests. Discord isn't just for gamers. It's just a way to be in contact with people, and to find others that share your interests.

Can be a little finnicky at times but overall this is my go-to app for talking with friends, making new ones, and getting into games like D&D and Destiny. I met some of my closest friends through Discord, and it's hard to remember what life was like before I had this app on my phone and PC

Tis an awesome platform to work together with friends when playing games. I play Wot blitz, and its an amazing tool to use when talking to clan members or platoon groups working together towards a goal, especially with Voice Chat, and I love how I can share links, pictures, and replays of games with my friends. It's also amazing what you can do with the detailed format of creating server groups and channels within those servers. It lets you make a clean organized place to talk and share content.

Best of the best for kicking it with my buddies in or out of a game. Great for mobile use as well. Not complicated and intuitive. Only problem I ever had was due to another program conflicting and fixed with changing priorities. Add groovy to your channel to share music with friends!

I've used discord for 3 years now and have had a great experience throughout. The ability to create servers and connect with friends is vastly better than other apps like skype and it is very easy to use. I would recommend this for anyone who needs an easy to use, secure messaging app.

Discord is great, and the mobile app version is great too. They recently added a Messenger-style bubble for calls, which is great. Everything else works fine. Only complaint is that pretty often, I don't get the notifications when I normally would on PC, when they're supposed to come to my phone. But that's a minor issue. :)

Discord should be the go-to app for creating groups for communication. The text chats and voice chats are easy to set up and easy to join. Video calling is seamless whether you're in a private call, group chat, or a server for any community. Keeping up with friends, family, or coworkers is super simple and the experience is clean and enjoyable overall.

I love the app. It has done wonders to connect gamers into a single platform. My only gripe is that the reply function is horrible. If every post could be a thread like Microsoft teams it would honestly be the ultimate gaming tool. I just hate when I am responding to someone from the previous night and there are 500 messages in between. It's impossible to keep in thread.

I use discord on my PC almost daily, and the app is really useful for staying up to date with my book club, RPG groups, and dank memes. They are improving the app all the time, and I love the quality of life features they are always adding. It's a very pleasant experience to use this app!

Fantastic app. Best messenger I've ever used. I spent a good chunk of my day on her every day and I'm now a part of several communities all the way from a group of my irl friends to a global community for a certain game. Incredibly easy to use and by far just a great app. Definitely recommend.

Honestly the best voice+chat system I have ever used. Super flexible and I use it every day for a variety of different things (gaming, online yoga sessions, DnD, keeping in touch with my family). I have never written a review for anything in my life, but considering I've used it for used with no issues, Discord deserves every 5 start rating it gets.

Discord is an amazing app with tons of amazing features. I am a part of a number of different servers and I love the customization options for each server. The voice chats are very well put together and the way they run text channels is very easy. Would HIGHLY recommend this app! 10/10

Great app, easy to use, and the dark mode is very easy on the eyes. I use this on a daily basis to talk with friends, and I feel like there's nothing as superior as discord when it comes to talking with people online. Their public servers aren't the best, but hey, you can freely create private servers, so you don't have to see anything from the public servers.

It's a wonderful app to use to stay in touch with friends, family and gamers BUT it has many issues. Things need to be fixed. We need you right now more than ever. Issues with: - connection -audio problems (can't hear others or vice versa) -glitches where you can't even open or use the app -The app itself glitches from time to time. I notice if I click on a friend to open a message, it opens something else, it isn't harmful but it can get rather annoying. -livestreaming/screensharing Pls fix

An amazing app, I absolutely adore it for talking to people. It gives you the option of talking in dms, and creating groups of up to 10 people, and also creating servers that can hold as many people as you can invite. With the option of creating invite links that can be posted anywhere, whether in your minecraft sever, or on another app. It does have the occasional glitch, and can be a bit laggy when switching between servers rapidly. Calls work well, and you can overlay the call over your games

Great way to talk to your friends while you game or find new friends that like things that you like too! Its come a long way you can stream watch others stream voice and video chat what more could you need. I love it and am on almost everyday to stay in touch with friends and family.

The random voice disconnects (which have gotten more frequent since 1/1/2020) are highly obnoxious. Not to mention the occasional issue that requires you to restart mobile devices after leaving a long voice chat because Discord refuses to release your device's sound capabilities, which locks you out of utilizing music players (happens most often when you get a phone call that comes in while you are in a voice channel). Other than that, it is amazing for text, image, and video sharing.

I've been a Member for 3 to 4 years, overall, it's a Great and easy to use app. -Good Security. [] -Link Social Networks (YouTube, Steam, etc) -Good Moderation. [] -Direct Messaging and Groups/Servers. [] -Not so Strict Censorship. [] -Guidelines and ToS are Fair -13 Years or Older only is fair, just to Avoid the Cringy Kids for once.

I love the desktop program and the app works just about as well with the few necessary UI changes needed to make the transition. Always adding new features, no ads, and really expanded to help people keep in contact during this time of crisis. Great app by a great team.

Discord is easy, seamless communication, pure and simple. Syncs perfectly between laptop and phone, so no need to get tethered to one device. Aimed at gamers, and includes lots of features that makes it ideal for us, but a good, stable text and voice-chat app is valuable for anyone imo. And there are servers for many topics, too. Game-based ones, for sure, but also groups for other things. I keep up with several webcomics through discord server announcements, for example.

It's free so can't really complain right? Weeeellll, for myself, and a lot of users of the phone app, the audio will suddenly cut out in voice channel (input and output) and you will have to leave and reconnect. Very frustrating in raids. Imo that makes this a highly unreliable client and in no way fit for high end activities requiring voice communication. Good for other purposes though.

Discord is A little confusing at first but I like how you can be part of different servers, send chat messages as well as private messages. It's easy to upload photos or whatever to share with others. I like how i can add a reaction to any individual post. The reactions are of every emoji available, not just heart or thumbs up, it's got everything. I like how I can mute certain channels so that way it's not always a notification popping up. And being able to see pinned messages like bookmarks.

The best communication app for non-commercial use. Discord and the app in general work wonderfully and provide the information idest range of perks in this category. However they have a tendency to push updates before they are ready and seem to have little regard for what the community actually wants both UI and feature wise. It is still the best program for communicating I have ever seen and I will likely never use anything else. I look forwards to the improvements they'll make in the future.

I got discord at the begging of last summer so that me and my friends could play dnd over the phone when we couldnt all meet up. This app is phenomenal. You can create well organized servers and keep your account private or you could join any of the amazing mega servers. The ability to tailor the app to your needs is phenominal.

Discord will constantly have something a Little Off about it. For me right now it's being regularly dropped from the audio of calls (anywhere between 1-3 times in a 3/4 hour session). That being said it's really the only thing that comes close to doing all it does well. I have group messages for friends and planning, servers for fandoms, d&d and bots; and breaking it into rooms and being able to set 18+ conditions up separately is really helpful. It's just pretty neat.

It's definitely the best app for communication I've personally used. Leagues better than Skype and other similar apps. It has a lot of features that are geared towards gamers, but I feel like just about anyone could utilize Discord for optimal messsaging. If you're looking for an alternative to other communication apps out there, I would 100% give it a shot.

I love using discord everyday as the main platform for social interaction. It feels welcoming every time I open it. It's constantly being updated to enhance the user's experience. I realize this review isn't too convincing with the bad wording, but I really love this app.

Great app! Works well with no significant bugs or issues that I've encountered so far. My friends and I use it for most of our in-game communications and it has become or main means of long distance communication during this period of increased isolation and social distancing.

Despite some bugs here and there oh, this continues to be one of the best communication resources I have ever used. My Hope Is that they expand their processes more and more mediums. If you're looking for something to use communication for gaming, Hangout, or what have you this is it.

Honestly this is the best app I've encountered, whether pc or mobile. It's great how you can send any file (8mb limit if I remember correctly?) through here. Rather than a call, you join voice chat lobbies, or go through text chat(s). You can easily organize members through 'roles' so you can easily tell whether they're whatever you wish for them to be. Say new members, mods, etc. It's easy to invite/join servers by clicking/copy-pasting a link. It's user friendly as well, and in no way clunky.

Very nicely designed and working platform for communication. Innovative chatrooms with many channels, permissions, and roles all while keeping it simple and smooth. All around 10/10 plus it is completely free. It's good for large groups or even just two people having a nice chat.

Near perfect. They've got a real good team managing the app version of Discord. They'll make necessary changes to the app every few years that only ever improves the app to a better experience. Even works on an old phone like the Samsung Galaxy Note 4. Good for gamers, school clubs/activities online, or friends wanting to keep in touch. Little bit more advanced than Skype, but anyone is capable of figuring it out.

One of the very best social gaming experiences out there. Join a group or start a group and start adding people that play the same games as you. Then you are all set to game with friends every day and have the best laughs along the way. Platform is ridiculously flexible with options: text, voice and video chat, privately, in small groups, or in large groups. Functions as a blog site, how to guides, group post site, Meme post site, special topic discussions, guild platform.... anything you need.

I enjoy using this apps.It helps me to communicate with people around the world without letting them having my number.But sometimes,there is a problem where i can't really hear the voice and when there are lots of people joining the voice call,It is hard kinda hard to hear all of their voice.

Great app for communication. You can make your own server in 2 seconds to chat with your friends. You can join an existing community related to your favorite game or topic. I love adding custom emojis to your servers and customize them. Audio calls are very clear. Live streaming your screen is also a great feature. All around I highly recommend it

But, yeah its really good, I love it.

This app is one of the, if not, the best app for communication. The voice quality is crystal clear, and server group calls are awesome. Oh, and you can use this on either pc or phone for calls, unlike whatsapp or insta.

Discord is AMAZING. No ads, all free, amazing quality, and perfect for people who want to chat. Discord gets messaging and voice calling and takes it to a whole new level. Download it! I got it and me and my friends LOVE IT. I also use it to chat in my favourite games!

Awesome! Discord isn't publicly traded and they do what they can to keep the base free, which is a ton of features. Unlimited server capacity for people, the only real limitation is file upload size, 8MB per is the limit, which is plenty for basic use. Thanks for staying awesome, discord!

I have the new UI update that Snapchat is testing and it makes the app MUCH worse. It's hard to navigate and unintuitive because some of the gestures are the same but not all, for example whenever I try to open a message I end up opening the map. Also, after taking a photo, the black bar at the bottom that fills the space where the menu used to be is ugly, poorly integrated, and makes my photos smaller. The old version was perfectly fine and the UX was so much better before I got this update.

I used to love the ap and I still do for the filters but I dont get notifications for snaps at all anymore. Ive reported the problem countless times. Still nothing fixes it and I never get a response for my reported issues. Very disappointing
